1
00:00:10,010 --> 00:00:14,097
In the last episode, our eternal singles
had a real tear-fest right?

2
00:00:14,180 --> 00:00:15,348
Like a faucet.

3
00:00:15,432 --> 00:00:17,642
Yes, it was also a day
when everyone got hurt very badly.

4
00:00:17,726 --> 00:00:20,270
It's about time everyone figured out
who they're going for,

5
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:22,689
but the picture's still murky.

6
00:00:22,772 --> 00:00:24,399
It's a messy situation.

7
00:00:25,233 --> 00:00:28,194
So as of right now, the couple
we have a good feeling about

8
00:00:28,278 --> 00:00:30,363
is Soo-hyun and Tae-hoon?

9
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:32,949
- That's right.
- Our blueberry smoothie couple.

10
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:35,493
For me, Hyuk-joon and Su-ji.

11
00:00:36,161 --> 00:00:37,871
For some reason, I keep thinking that

12
00:00:37,954 --> 00:00:40,832
Su-ji and Jung-yun
might actually end up together.

13
00:00:40,915 --> 00:00:43,710
I think there's a really good chance
Su-ji might really open her heart

14
00:00:43,793 --> 00:00:46,379
to Jung-yun after seeing
his unwavering commitment.

15
00:00:46,463 --> 00:00:48,381
I agree. Su-ji and Jung-yun.

16
00:00:48,465 --> 00:00:51,801
When Hyuk-joon and Han-ju were talking
at the end of the last episode,

17
00:00:51,885 --> 00:00:56,056
I felt that Han-ju looked calm
for the first time on this show.

18
00:00:56,139 --> 00:00:57,265
- Yes.
- Ah.

19
00:00:57,348 --> 00:01:00,310
So I'd be willing to bet that these two
might end up connecting together

20
00:01:00,393 --> 00:01:01,311
in the end.

21
00:01:01,394 --> 00:01:04,272
Could Jeong-eun and Jin-woo
be another possibility?

22
00:01:04,355 --> 00:01:06,858
To spark something off between these two,
I feel like one of them

23
00:01:06,941 --> 00:01:09,027
has to take some kind of action,
so I don't know.

24
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:11,237
But, you know, on <i>Better Late Than Single</i>,

25
00:01:11,321 --> 00:01:14,240
everything is totally unpredictable,
right up until the last day.

26
00:01:14,324 --> 00:01:15,909
- Everything could change.
- Everything could change.

27
00:01:15,992 --> 00:01:18,912
Everything could change as soon as
we start playing this episode, even.

28
00:01:18,995 --> 00:01:20,205
For crying out loud.

29
00:01:20,288 --> 00:01:22,540
DATE
JUNG-YUN AND SU-JI

30
00:01:22,624 --> 00:01:24,125
This must be it.

31
00:01:26,544 --> 00:01:28,171
Here you are. After you.

32
00:01:28,254 --> 00:01:30,048
Thank you kindly.

33
00:01:30,131 --> 00:01:31,591
I hope Jung-yun can cheer up.

34
00:01:34,928 --> 00:01:36,096
There's a piano!

35
00:01:36,179 --> 00:01:37,597
Oh, his specialty.

36
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:40,141
This is great! Let's go, Jung-yun.

37
00:01:44,854 --> 00:01:47,148
Mmm. This is good.

38
00:01:47,232 --> 00:01:48,316
It is good.

39
00:01:50,193 --> 00:01:54,489
I told myself to put aside
any hard feelings or whatever,

40
00:01:54,572 --> 00:01:57,492
and to focus on the task at hand.

41
00:01:58,118 --> 00:02:01,955
I did hit a… what you could call
a bit of a speed bump,

42
00:02:02,038 --> 00:02:05,834
but in the end,
I resolved to stay the course.

43
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:07,502
- Wow.
- That's right.

44
00:02:07,585 --> 00:02:09,879
That's right. They're here
because they chose each other.

45
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:11,422
He needs to be confident now.

46
00:02:18,930 --> 00:02:19,973
Oh, it's snowing.

47
00:02:21,099 --> 00:02:22,517
Or is it hail?

48
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:25,186
- Even the weather's dramatic.
- I know.

49
00:02:31,401 --> 00:02:33,194
- Huh? What's wrong?
- Su-ji?

50
00:02:34,696 --> 00:02:36,573
- Actually…
- Uh-huh?

51
00:02:36,656 --> 00:02:38,241
There was something I wanted to ask you.

52
00:02:38,324 --> 00:02:41,536
- Oh, ask away. Let's hear it.
- Yesterday, you told me…

53
00:02:41,619 --> 00:02:44,289
- Uh-huh.
- …that you like someone who's strong.

54
00:02:44,372 --> 00:02:45,206
Mm-hmm.

55
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:46,416
YESTERDAY AFTERNOON

56
00:02:46,499 --> 00:02:48,209
I want her to be a strong person.

57
00:02:48,293 --> 00:02:52,172
I don't think
I'd feel very attracted to someone

58
00:02:52,255 --> 00:02:55,592
who gets swayed too easily
by other people.

59
00:02:55,675 --> 00:02:57,051
I see. Hmm.

60
00:02:59,095 --> 00:03:02,765
But what's your definition
of a strong person? I'd like to find out.

61
00:03:02,849 --> 00:03:06,060
Um, someone who has
a clear set of standards.

62
00:03:06,144 --> 00:03:08,730
- Standards?
- Yeah, someone with clear standards.

63
00:03:08,813 --> 00:03:10,732
When they make decisions or choices?

64
00:03:10,815 --> 00:03:11,816
Well…

65
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:14,694
that's part of it.

66
00:03:15,820 --> 00:03:16,779
But the thing is,

67
00:03:16,863 --> 00:03:19,115
I don't think I'm actually
that strong of a person myself.

68
00:03:19,199 --> 00:03:20,658
Mmm.

69
00:03:20,742 --> 00:03:23,995
Which is why I would ideally like to be
with someone who is strong,

70
00:03:24,078 --> 00:03:25,455
so we have a balance.

71
00:03:25,538 --> 00:03:28,625
Yes, but yesterday,
you said you liked strong people,

72
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:30,960
and I thought to myself,

73
00:03:31,044 --> 00:03:32,629
"Oh, I don't think that's me."

74
00:03:32,712 --> 00:03:33,546
Right.

75
00:03:33,630 --> 00:03:35,590
- Why is she saying this?
- I know, right?

76
00:03:35,673 --> 00:03:38,843
But for me, you see… How should I put it?

77
00:03:38,927 --> 00:03:42,805
I really enjoy listening
and being there for people.

78
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:44,599
Like, hearing them out.

79
00:03:45,308 --> 00:03:50,146
So, um, even if their emotions are, say,
in turmoil or wavering,

80
00:03:50,230 --> 00:03:54,150
I've always thought it's possible

81
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,318
to work through it

82
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:58,279
by talking with each other.

83
00:03:59,656 --> 00:04:01,991
- Jung-yun's being very cautious.
- Yeah.

84
00:04:02,742 --> 00:04:03,993
What I mean is,

85
00:04:04,077 --> 00:04:07,330
how can a person be strong all the time?

86
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:09,207
- Right, right.
- That's good.

87
00:04:09,958 --> 00:04:10,917
Mmm.

88
00:04:11,417 --> 00:04:12,919
Does that answer your question?

89
00:04:13,002 --> 00:04:14,504
Yes. I appreciate that.

90
00:04:15,338 --> 00:04:17,006
Thank you.

91
00:04:19,133 --> 00:04:22,095
If you have anything else
you want to ask me, feel free.

92
00:04:23,930 --> 00:04:25,223
Mmm…

93
00:04:28,393 --> 00:04:29,644
The weather's nice.

94
00:04:30,270 --> 00:04:32,772
Ugh, the energy just isn't picking up.

95
00:04:33,648 --> 00:04:35,316
It suddenly went from snowing to sunny.

96
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:37,735
Yeah, and then back to hailing
and then sunny again.

97
00:04:37,819 --> 00:04:38,736
Yeah.

98
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:43,283
There's no laughter or anything.

99
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:45,034
Nothing.

100
00:04:48,204 --> 00:04:49,455
What is it, Su-ji?

101
00:04:49,956 --> 00:04:52,125
- She looks really preoccupied.
- Yeah.

102
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:02,468
Uh, you know how we played the, uh,
Towel Game before you arrived?

103
00:05:02,552 --> 00:05:03,386
Yeah.

104
00:05:03,469 --> 00:05:06,097
During the game, we talked about, like,

105
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:08,349
the times we'd been hurt and stuff.

106
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:09,684
Right.

107
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:12,186
For me, there was this one time where,

108
00:05:12,270 --> 00:05:14,772
if the person had told me sooner,

109
00:05:14,856 --> 00:05:20,153
I, uh, would've been able to
give up earlier or something.

110
00:05:20,903 --> 00:05:25,366
I found out she had feelings
for someone else.

111
00:05:25,450 --> 00:05:26,617
Right, right.

112
00:05:26,701 --> 00:05:31,372
So when I found out
through the grapevine later,

113
00:05:31,456 --> 00:05:33,458
I couldn't really understand why.

114
00:05:33,541 --> 00:05:34,834
Right.

115
00:05:34,917 --> 00:05:37,128
Why she couldn't have just been…

116
00:05:37,879 --> 00:05:38,921
up-front about it.

117
00:05:39,005 --> 00:05:40,006
Yeah.

118
00:05:40,590 --> 00:05:43,509
So, I think that really…

119
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:45,845
scarred me.

120
00:05:47,722 --> 00:05:49,682
- I understand.
- Yeah.

121
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:51,851
It's kind of similar
to what's happening here too.

122
00:05:51,934 --> 00:05:53,603
Yeah, so unfortunate.

123
00:06:01,861 --> 00:06:03,780
Su-ji. What is it, Su-ji?

124
00:06:03,863 --> 00:06:06,366
Ugh. Something's not right here.

125
00:06:06,449 --> 00:06:08,326
The vibe just isn't there.

126
00:06:11,829 --> 00:06:13,790
Hey, no. Don't. Don't play the piano.

127
00:06:13,873 --> 00:06:17,001
No, this is totally not the time.
Please don't. Now's not the time.

128
00:06:17,085 --> 00:06:19,921
- Uh, should I play a piece on the piano?
- What?

129
00:06:20,004 --> 00:06:21,798
No, don't do it, don't do it.

130
00:06:23,925 --> 00:06:26,844
I told you I wanted to play
the piano for you, right?

131
00:06:28,221 --> 00:06:29,055
That's right.

132
00:06:29,138 --> 00:06:31,307
But I don't want to make
you feel uncomfortable.

133
00:06:31,391 --> 00:06:33,476
What do you mean?
You're just playing the piano for me.

134
00:06:33,559 --> 00:06:35,728
- That's true, but…
- So why would I feel uncomfortable?

135
00:06:35,812 --> 00:06:37,146
It's not like it has some huge meaning.

136
00:06:37,230 --> 00:06:39,065
- Oh, no. Nothing like that, but…
- Mmm, right.

137
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,359
Could you play it for me now?

138
00:06:41,442 --> 00:06:43,820
- Should I?
- Would you play me a piece?

139
00:06:43,903 --> 00:06:45,863
Yeah, I think you should.

140
00:06:46,572 --> 00:06:48,449
I'll just play one piece.

141
00:06:48,533 --> 00:06:50,993
He did say he wanted to play
the piano for someone he liked.

142
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:54,163
- All right, here goes.
- Okay.

143
00:07:21,065 --> 00:07:24,527
I played her a piece called "Reminiscent."

144
00:07:25,653 --> 00:07:29,282
The title refers to reminiscence

145
00:07:29,365 --> 00:07:32,535
or memories and that kind of thing.

146
00:07:32,618 --> 00:07:35,204
I played it for her, I think,

147
00:07:35,288 --> 00:07:38,791
in the hope that when I later
look back on this moment,

148
00:07:38,875 --> 00:07:42,545
it will bring to mind… nice memories.

149
00:07:54,182 --> 00:07:58,227
I was really quite, quite nervous
as I was playing,

150
00:07:58,311 --> 00:08:01,814
and my hands were shaking a little.

151
00:08:04,358 --> 00:08:06,611
- Is this really the mood you want to set?
- Yeah, yeah.

152
00:08:06,694 --> 00:08:08,905
I think I've heard this song before.

153
00:08:08,988 --> 00:08:12,617
After the incident yesterday,

154
00:08:12,700 --> 00:08:15,953
I actually spent a lot of time
thinking by myself,

155
00:08:16,787 --> 00:08:19,207
but the things that happened today

156
00:08:20,249 --> 00:08:23,461
were good enough to

157
00:08:24,045 --> 00:08:26,172
make me forget all about that.

158
00:08:29,258 --> 00:08:30,843
The best thing about it?

159
00:08:32,887 --> 00:08:34,263
Hmm…

160
00:08:36,432 --> 00:08:39,477
The piano was
the most memorable part. Yes.

161
00:08:40,436 --> 00:08:44,690
But the only thing I felt was
that I was comfortable.

162
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:46,651
I feel so comfortable when I'm with him

163
00:08:46,734 --> 00:08:48,986
that I don't feel anything else.

164
00:08:52,073 --> 00:08:53,241
So…

165
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:56,285
I was kinda like, "What's going on?"

166
00:08:57,662 --> 00:08:59,038
Oh, there's just no spark.

167
00:08:59,121 --> 00:09:01,332
Right, the huge impact
Hyuk-joon must've had.

168
00:09:01,415 --> 00:09:02,583
Exactly, yeah.

169
00:09:02,667 --> 00:09:05,461
You know, some dates just feel
really comfortable,

170
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:08,005
while others make you feel
awkward and excited

171
00:09:08,089 --> 00:09:10,383
and give you that
"butterflies in your stomach" emotions.

172
00:09:10,466 --> 00:09:12,927
Not to mention, when you play the piano,

173
00:09:13,010 --> 00:09:16,472
your audience usually feels
all of your emotions, your reactions.

174
00:09:16,556 --> 00:09:17,390
That's right.

175
00:09:17,473 --> 00:09:20,935
But this whole performance is
so milquetoast, I'm getting the feeling…

176
00:09:21,519 --> 00:09:26,691
Su-ji might not be getting the closure
she actually needs to forget…

177
00:09:27,441 --> 00:09:30,611
to forget and actually move on instead of
of focusing her energy on Jung-yun.

178
00:09:30,695 --> 00:09:32,280
- Right.
- Do you think?

179
00:09:32,363 --> 00:09:33,698
DATE
JIN-WOO AND JEONG-EUN

180
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:36,742
Jin-woo and Jeong-eun.
What will the vibe be like there?

181
00:09:37,618 --> 00:09:38,869
Would you like a napkin?

182
00:09:38,953 --> 00:09:40,913
I think these two look good together too.

183
00:09:40,997 --> 00:09:42,373
- They do.
- It's fresh, no?

184
00:09:42,456 --> 00:09:44,083
Would you like a macaroon?

185
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:45,668
I'll move it off to the side.

186
00:09:46,586 --> 00:09:48,754
He's so attentive.
Oh, he's really attentive.

187
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:52,341
- Did you write something?
- What do you mean?

188
00:09:52,425 --> 00:09:54,635
Did you write to someone?
At the Post Office?

189
00:09:54,719 --> 00:09:56,846
- I wrote a letter for the first time.
- Mmm.

190
00:09:56,929 --> 00:09:59,348
Huh? Jeong-eun, did you use a coupon?

191
00:09:59,432 --> 00:10:00,266
THIS MORNING

192
00:10:00,349 --> 00:10:01,434
Oh.

193
00:10:01,517 --> 00:10:02,560
- On Jin-woo?
- Wow.

194
00:10:07,189 --> 00:10:09,525
What I found was a letter
written by Jeong-eun,

195
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:12,194
and it was accompanying
the good-luck fish.

196
00:10:12,278 --> 00:10:14,405
You mean Jeong-eun
put herself out there like that?

197
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:15,323
Yeah.

198
00:10:15,406 --> 00:10:17,575
She wrote she was grateful
I was so understanding

199
00:10:17,658 --> 00:10:19,702
of her somewhat complicated situation,

200
00:10:19,785 --> 00:10:23,539
and because of that, she would also
try to express her feelings for me.

201
00:10:23,623 --> 00:10:25,124
She hoped that…

202
00:10:25,207 --> 00:10:28,210
the good-luck fish would bring me luck
and included it with the letter.

203
00:10:28,294 --> 00:10:30,755
- Oh. Well, that's pretty bold.
- It is pretty bold.

204
00:10:30,838 --> 00:10:34,091
Totally. I think Jin-woo mentioned
he wanted to receive this, right?

205
00:10:34,175 --> 00:10:36,218
- Oh, and she remembered that!
- Yeah.

206
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:39,472
I was so happy to get it that I took
a picture of it and hung it up.

207
00:10:40,473 --> 00:10:41,724
That's the right reaction.

208
00:10:41,807 --> 00:10:43,559
Exactly the reaction this gift
should bring out.

209
00:10:43,643 --> 00:10:45,728
If you're interested in someone,
this is how you react.

210
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:54,987
- So he chose you. Hyuk-joon.
- Right, right. Yeah.

211
00:10:55,071 --> 00:10:58,074
Ah, that ate at him.
He must want to know how it went.

212
00:10:58,157 --> 00:11:00,618
And Hyuk-joon was also

213
00:11:01,452 --> 00:11:05,081
one of the two guys
that you chose on your date, so…

214
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:08,459
I was kind of worried you had feelings.

215
00:11:10,336 --> 00:11:13,422
That you had developed feelings before I…

216
00:11:14,256 --> 00:11:16,217
even got a chance to give it a shot.

217
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:18,761
This is kind of…

218
00:11:19,512 --> 00:11:23,432
just my own personal experience.

219
00:11:24,392 --> 00:11:26,769
But before I came here,

220
00:11:27,812 --> 00:11:28,979
I really lacked confidence.

221
00:11:29,063 --> 00:11:30,106
Right, right.

222
00:11:30,189 --> 00:11:33,693
Like, even if I approached
someone I liked,

223
00:11:33,776 --> 00:11:35,027
it wouldn't work out.

224
00:11:35,111 --> 00:11:39,365
So I really worked on that
to fix the issue before starting the show.

225
00:11:39,448 --> 00:11:41,158
I got counseling and stuff,

226
00:11:41,242 --> 00:11:43,911
and I was determined to do a good job.

227
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:46,580
But yesterday, when that happened,

228
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:48,999
I just didn't know what to do.

229
00:11:49,959 --> 00:11:53,546
I kept feeling like
I would go back to my old self again.

230
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:54,672
Mmm.

231
00:11:55,464 --> 00:11:58,843
Wow. He's laying out
such a heartfelt story for her.

232
00:11:58,926 --> 00:12:01,512
So all day yesterday was tough for me.

233
00:12:02,638 --> 00:12:05,516
I don't blame you for feeling that way.

234
00:12:07,393 --> 00:12:09,687
- But my thoughts are in order now.
- Oh, yeah?

235
00:12:10,187 --> 00:12:12,565
Getting out of that place and clearing
my head seems to have helped.

236
00:12:12,648 --> 00:12:13,691
I know, right?

237
00:12:13,774 --> 00:12:16,444
Out of all the guys, though,
you seem to be the one

238
00:12:16,527 --> 00:12:19,780
who communicates the most frankly
about your emotions

239
00:12:19,864 --> 00:12:21,949
without worrying about
what response you'll get.

240
00:12:22,032 --> 00:12:23,909
- Oh, really? Oh. Wow.
- Yeah.

241
00:12:25,828 --> 00:12:27,580
- And I really appreciate that.
- Hmm.

242
00:12:28,205 --> 00:12:30,750
- Glad to know that's how I come across.
- Yeah.

243
00:12:31,500 --> 00:12:35,755
Yeah, so I appreciate it when
you confidently step up and take charge.

244
00:12:35,838 --> 00:12:37,089
Ooh!

245
00:12:37,173 --> 00:12:39,592
It sounds like she's talking
to a potential romantic partner.

246
00:12:39,675 --> 00:12:42,303
Do you have an idea of how you looked

247
00:12:42,386 --> 00:12:45,055
when you first arrived here?

248
00:12:45,139 --> 00:12:47,141
- Me?
- Yeah, how you looked.

249
00:12:47,808 --> 00:12:50,269
- You made a strong impression on me.
- Oh, did I?

250
00:12:50,352 --> 00:12:52,772
Yeah. I tried really hard
to hang around near you.

251
00:12:52,855 --> 00:12:54,023
Oh, yeah?

252
00:12:54,106 --> 00:12:56,400
Uh, I sat next to you
when we were all gathered in the Yard.

253
00:12:56,484 --> 00:12:57,943
Oh, that's right. You sat next to me.

254
00:12:58,027 --> 00:13:00,571
- Oh, they're joined together.
- Same color.

255
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:03,365
That's right.

256
00:13:03,908 --> 00:13:06,368
- How should we sit?
- He did sit next to her.

257
00:13:10,873 --> 00:13:13,083
If you put a mask on after eating this…

258
00:13:13,167 --> 00:13:14,835
Don't ask me how I know.

259
00:13:15,461 --> 00:13:17,505
- I told you, you're the most proactive.
- Hmm.

260
00:13:18,756 --> 00:13:23,177
So do you not have anyone else you want
to get to know before we leave here? Or…

261
00:13:23,260 --> 00:13:25,012
- No, not for me.
- No one at all?

262
00:13:25,095 --> 00:13:26,138
- Mmm.
- Hmm.

263
00:13:26,222 --> 00:13:28,349
There's nothing left for me to explore.

264
00:13:29,183 --> 00:13:32,186
To me, what I find appealing
about Jin-woo is this:

265
00:13:32,269 --> 00:13:36,607
It may happen that he will lose
interest in me altogether,

266
00:13:36,690 --> 00:13:39,401
but I don't think his attention
will waver due to another girl.

267
00:13:40,820 --> 00:13:42,947
Would you like a patch
that helps with puffiness?

268
00:13:43,030 --> 00:13:44,949
- Oh, yes, pretty please.
- Yes, please.

269
00:13:45,032 --> 00:13:46,534
- Aren't they for mornings?
- Thank you.

270
00:13:46,617 --> 00:13:47,910
One now and one in the morning?

271
00:13:47,993 --> 00:13:49,703
- You lost this, right?
- Oh!

272
00:13:50,204 --> 00:13:51,956
Thank you.

273
00:13:52,039 --> 00:13:54,458
- Don't forget to take it this time.
- Of course I won't.

274
00:13:55,125 --> 00:13:57,044
On my way here,
I thought it would be great…

275
00:13:57,878 --> 00:14:00,506
if I were here for being picked
by someone I was interested in.

276
00:14:00,589 --> 00:14:03,467
- And the thing is, I also picked you.
- Oh, really? Oh.

277
00:14:03,551 --> 00:14:06,178
I voted for you when we went together.

278
00:14:06,262 --> 00:14:08,222
He's showing his interest.

279
00:14:08,305 --> 00:14:09,807
Wow. He's been consistent.

280
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:12,101
To be honest, before I came here,

281
00:14:12,184 --> 00:14:14,770
I always thought
I wouldn't be able to date a student.

282
00:14:14,854 --> 00:14:18,858
But despite thinking that,
I became attracted to him,

283
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:23,195
which makes me realize it is proof
that Jin-woo has huge appeal.

284
00:14:23,279 --> 00:14:24,530
Aw!

285
00:14:25,281 --> 00:14:26,740
Oh, that's nice.

286
00:14:26,824 --> 00:14:30,744
This one-on-one date off the grounds
allowed us to have deeper conversations,

287
00:14:30,828 --> 00:14:33,914
and I could express my feelings
in different ways,

288
00:14:33,998 --> 00:14:34,999
so it was really good.

289
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:38,168
I just looked at Jeong-eun's face

290
00:14:38,836 --> 00:14:40,838
and thought about
how happy I was to be there.

291
00:14:40,921 --> 00:14:42,590
Oh, aren't these two a done deal?

292
00:14:42,673 --> 00:14:44,800
I was Jeong-eun's designated Cupid.

293
00:14:44,884 --> 00:14:48,304
And previously,
she was concerned about whether

294
00:14:48,387 --> 00:14:51,056
she'd be able to actually
really feel the spark.

295
00:14:51,140 --> 00:14:52,683
You know, the emotions.

296
00:14:52,766 --> 00:14:56,437
But I can see how her eyes are gradually
changing as she listens to Jin-woo.

297
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:59,690
Yes, I can sense the change.
I have a good feeling about these two.

298
00:14:59,773 --> 00:15:02,026
I really like that he doesn't confuse her
in any way.

299
00:15:02,109 --> 00:15:04,486
When it comes to these two,
I think we can relax.

300
00:15:08,407 --> 00:15:10,200
Wait, what? Who is this?

301
00:15:11,452 --> 00:15:13,078
- Seung-hyun.
- Seung-hyun.

302
00:15:19,668 --> 00:15:21,503
I was feeling a little lonely.

303
00:15:22,004 --> 00:15:24,548
Everyone had left, and I felt alone.

304
00:15:24,632 --> 00:15:27,384
My roommate was gone,
and there was no one next door to me.

305
00:15:27,468 --> 00:15:30,179
Yeah. And I know he said
he was okay, but I don't buy it.

306
00:15:30,262 --> 00:15:32,681
With all that's happened,
how can he truly be okay?

307
00:15:32,765 --> 00:15:34,099
I'm not troubled.

308
00:15:34,183 --> 00:15:38,228
I think I was troubled
up until the point Su-ji rejected me.

309
00:15:38,312 --> 00:15:41,148
But since then,
I've actually felt relieved.

310
00:15:44,777 --> 00:15:47,237
Oh, so Seung-hyun turned out to be
the lead character

311
00:15:47,321 --> 00:15:48,656
in the next music video.

312
00:15:48,739 --> 00:15:51,158
That's right. We have a new music video.

313
00:15:56,789 --> 00:15:59,583
- Oh, from day three to day five?
- Yes, that's so true.

314
00:15:59,667 --> 00:16:03,045
- Soo-hyun's first-impression pick.
- Wow, things have shifted around a lot.

315
00:16:03,128 --> 00:16:04,213
Hyun-seo.

316
00:16:06,048 --> 00:16:09,093
Jeong-eun went on a date with him too.
"Very satisfied."

317
00:16:14,264 --> 00:16:16,475
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

318
00:16:16,558 --> 00:16:18,310
The guy who's held
four women in his heart.

319
00:16:18,394 --> 00:16:21,271
- Oh, this is too funny.
- A lot of women have left him, yeah.

320
00:16:22,147 --> 00:16:23,482
The ones left behind.

321
00:16:23,565 --> 00:16:26,110
I wonder what kind
of dates they're all having.

322
00:16:29,154 --> 00:16:30,906
I wonder how they're feeling right now.

323
00:16:30,990 --> 00:16:32,950
I actually really don't know.

324
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:34,284
What don't you know?

325
00:16:34,368 --> 00:16:37,287
- Is that Jae-seo lying there?
- Oh, is he under the desk?

326
00:16:37,371 --> 00:16:40,124
I just don't want to do anything anymore.

327
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:43,711
Hmm? Why?
Why don't you want to do anything?

328
00:16:46,046 --> 00:16:48,507
I don't know what I'm feeling anymore.

329
00:16:49,842 --> 00:16:52,845
If there was a situation
where I had to pick someone,

330
00:16:53,679 --> 00:16:57,057
I wouldn't even know who to choose.

331
00:16:57,141 --> 00:16:59,560
Hyun-seo's voice sounds even more subdued.

332
00:16:59,643 --> 00:17:03,397
- Her emotional state now is…
- That's where I'm at.

333
00:17:04,523 --> 00:17:06,608
I know. And we have…

334
00:17:07,276 --> 00:17:10,612
We still have coupons for the Post Office

335
00:17:10,696 --> 00:17:12,656
and the other stuff.

336
00:17:14,033 --> 00:17:15,993
I don't know if I'll…

337
00:17:16,618 --> 00:17:20,164
be able to spend them all before I leave.

338
00:17:20,247 --> 00:17:22,791
Actually, I was about to spend them.

339
00:17:22,875 --> 00:17:25,127
- Really?
- But I think it's a good thing I didn't.

340
00:17:25,210 --> 00:17:26,378
Mmm…

341
00:17:29,423 --> 00:17:32,217
You know, I wish today would be…

342
00:17:32,301 --> 00:17:33,552
I wish people…

343
00:17:34,553 --> 00:17:36,722
could have at least one day
without suffering.

344
00:17:37,389 --> 00:17:39,600
Some people were still suffering
as of yesterday.

345
00:17:39,683 --> 00:17:42,144
Everyone's happy now except for us.
What are you talking about?

346
00:17:42,227 --> 00:17:44,646
- That might not be the case.
- What are you saying?

347
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:46,899
- Those guys are on top of the world.
- You think so?

348
00:17:46,982 --> 00:17:49,193
Yes, they're on a date
because they picked each other.

349
00:17:49,276 --> 00:17:50,360
That's right.

350
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:54,406
- I should just be worrying about myself.
- Exactly.

351
00:17:54,490 --> 00:17:56,617
Us here,
we just need to worry about ourselves.

352
00:17:56,700 --> 00:18:00,245
There's no way these guys
haven't fully made up their minds, right?

353
00:18:00,329 --> 00:18:02,331
I think they're pretty much a done deal.

354
00:18:02,414 --> 00:18:03,957
- You think so?
- The couples on dates now?

355
00:18:04,041 --> 00:18:05,793
- Yeah.
- I don't think so, actually.

356
00:18:05,876 --> 00:18:08,712
Come on, based on the vibes,
they were pretty much…

357
00:18:08,796 --> 00:18:11,715
Well, maybe that's not the case
for every couple.

358
00:18:12,341 --> 00:18:16,762
The final… The final decision could still
possibly change for some of them.

359
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:18,222
That's so true.

360
00:18:18,305 --> 00:18:21,308
There are people who change
their minds out of the blue.

361
00:18:22,726 --> 00:18:25,562
Ugh, I'm worried about what's to come.

362
00:18:25,646 --> 00:18:28,565
- Yeah.
- About what it is I should do.

363
00:18:30,442 --> 00:18:33,153
If I were Hyun-seo,
I'd feel so lost right now.

364
00:18:33,237 --> 00:18:36,156
I know. Ugh. Poor, poor Hyun-seo.

365
00:18:36,949 --> 00:18:38,534
Thank you for today.

366
00:18:38,617 --> 00:18:39,993
- See you in a bit.
- Sure.

367
00:18:40,077 --> 00:18:41,954
- I had a good time today.
- Me too.

368
00:18:42,037 --> 00:18:45,207
- A meaningful conversation.
- For me, it was.

369
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:47,835
- That's what I said. It was meaningful.
- Okay.

370
00:18:47,918 --> 00:18:50,337
- See you in a bit. See you shortly.
- Sure.

371
00:18:50,420 --> 00:18:51,713
- See you in a bit.
- Sure.

372
00:18:52,589 --> 00:18:55,843
And then the second you get home,
you're like, "Hey, you guys!"

373
00:18:55,926 --> 00:18:58,512
- Soo-hyun's back.
- Is that you, Soo-hyun?

374
00:18:58,595 --> 00:19:01,140
- Oh, you're back.
- Oh, hello.

375
00:19:01,223 --> 00:19:02,641
How was it?

376
00:19:02,724 --> 00:19:04,935
- I have a lot to tell you.
- Oh, really?

377
00:19:05,018 --> 00:19:06,645
We all have a lot to talk about right now.

378
00:19:06,728 --> 00:19:07,855
- Really?
- Yeah.

379
00:19:07,938 --> 00:19:10,107
- What'd you do?
- We went to a café.

380
00:19:10,190 --> 00:19:12,609
We did too. We also went to a café.

381
00:19:13,152 --> 00:19:15,154
- Yeah, Life4Cuts.
- No. Just the café.

382
00:19:15,237 --> 00:19:16,280
Did you take any photos?

383
00:19:17,197 --> 00:19:18,657
The photo booths?

384
00:19:18,740 --> 00:19:22,202
Man, this is almost like
the official start of a relationship.

385
00:19:22,286 --> 00:19:23,829
Two, one. Oh!

386
00:19:26,582 --> 00:19:29,042
I just smiled.

387
00:19:30,043 --> 00:19:32,337
- They're nice photos.
- They're really cute.

388
00:19:32,421 --> 00:19:33,463
This one's cute.

389
00:19:33,547 --> 00:19:36,967
It's cute that they're so awkward
about posing.

390
00:19:38,635 --> 00:19:39,636
What?

391
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:41,763
- Don't tell anyone.
- What? What is it?

392
00:19:41,847 --> 00:19:43,557
I honestly had so much fun.

393
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:45,184
Oh, for God's sake.

394
00:19:45,267 --> 00:19:48,020
- Did you guys hold hands?
- No, we didn't.

395
00:19:48,103 --> 00:19:50,022
- Oh, you didn't?
- What are you talking about?

396
00:19:50,105 --> 00:19:52,107
How could you ask that
after seeing the photos?

397
00:19:52,858 --> 00:19:54,651
Forget about hands.

398
00:19:54,735 --> 00:19:56,236
We didn't even brush shoulders.

399
00:19:57,779 --> 00:19:59,281
We didn't even link arms.

400
00:20:00,407 --> 00:20:03,368
I had so much fun talking
with Tae-hoon on the date

401
00:20:03,452 --> 00:20:05,370
that nothing else entered my mind.

402
00:20:05,454 --> 00:20:07,289
That's such a positive take on it.

403
00:20:07,372 --> 00:20:11,919
You see, I've never
taken photos like that ever,

404
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:13,795
not even with my dad.

405
00:20:13,879 --> 00:20:16,340
- It was my first time ever, so…
- Oh, so they fist-bumped.

406
00:20:16,423 --> 00:20:20,052
Well, I would say I had fun,
but I don't know how he felt.

407
00:20:20,135 --> 00:20:23,931
I mean, I can't make him my boyfriend
just because I like him, you know?

408
00:20:24,014 --> 00:20:27,017
So I'll just continue
to do my best till the end.

409
00:20:27,100 --> 00:20:28,268
Oh!

410
00:20:28,352 --> 00:20:31,271
- Talking about a boyfriend?
- Oh, boy…

411
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:33,148
I hope Tae-hoon liked it too.

412
00:20:33,232 --> 00:20:35,442
I'm curious about Tae-hoon.
I want to know what he thought.

413
00:20:37,736 --> 00:20:39,655
- Wow, look at that.
- What's this?

414
00:20:39,738 --> 00:20:41,782
- Wow.
- Is it some special occasion today?

415
00:20:41,865 --> 00:20:43,575
- Ooh.
- Wow.

416
00:20:43,659 --> 00:20:44,743
Galbi-jjim?

417
00:20:44,826 --> 00:20:48,497
- No way. Ganjang-gejang.
- Gejang? It's so fancy.

418
00:20:48,580 --> 00:20:51,458
- Wow!
- Are we finally getting a feast too?

419
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:53,710
Hello. Everything here looks so delicious.

420
00:20:53,794 --> 00:20:55,837
- I would call this a feast.
- It looks good.

421
00:20:55,921 --> 00:20:59,007
It's the first time they're giving us
good food without discrimination.

422
00:20:59,091 --> 00:21:00,092
I know.

423
00:21:00,175 --> 00:21:02,719
They do really get a lot
of great food at Sparks House.

424
00:21:02,803 --> 00:21:04,179
Oh, that's right, that's right.

425
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:06,431
Many of these guys
haven't had food like this yet.

426
00:21:06,515 --> 00:21:07,766
Shouldn't we start?

427
00:21:07,849 --> 00:21:10,102
- Bon appétit.
- Bon appétit.

428
00:21:10,185 --> 00:21:11,895
Enjoy your meal, everyone.

429
00:21:12,771 --> 00:21:14,523
- Well, Su-ji likes it.
- Gosh.

430
00:21:20,862 --> 00:21:23,615
Ah. Sorry, trainer. It's just for tonight.

431
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:31,290
- It's not a competition, Jae-seo.
- Yeah.

432
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:33,000
Eating's a good investment.

433
00:21:33,083 --> 00:21:35,168
I'm not sure about me, though.

434
00:21:36,003 --> 00:21:38,505
- Is there more?
- I thought there was nothing left.

435
00:21:38,588 --> 00:21:40,132
It says, "Empty."

436
00:21:40,841 --> 00:21:42,259
- You want some?
- Huh? Sure.

437
00:21:42,342 --> 00:21:43,552
Big or small?

438
00:21:43,635 --> 00:21:45,429
- Yeah, that one.
- This one? Is it too small?

439
00:21:45,512 --> 00:21:47,014
- Oh, I'll just take it.
- Potatoes?

440
00:21:47,097 --> 00:21:49,558
Geez, I'm sure he's capable
of serving himself potatoes.

441
00:21:49,641 --> 00:21:51,268
She's taking good care of him, though.

442
00:21:51,351 --> 00:21:53,520
Gosh, these two are basically
giving couple vibes.

443
00:21:57,482 --> 00:21:59,860
- Is it good?
- Mm-hmm. I really like this food.

444
00:21:59,943 --> 00:22:02,279
- Tae-hoon's a man of few words.
- He is.

445
00:22:02,362 --> 00:22:03,363
Yeah.

446
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:07,409
We're the only ones
who went to a Life4Cuts.

447
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:09,286
No one else went to a Life4Cuts.

448
00:22:10,162 --> 00:22:12,789
Well, I'm sure the others

449
00:22:12,873 --> 00:22:14,791
did something more, uh…
something different.

450
00:22:14,875 --> 00:22:16,209
Did they just eat?

451
00:22:16,293 --> 00:22:19,671
Well, I asked them what they did,
and they just said they went to a café.

452
00:22:19,755 --> 00:22:21,631
I asked about Life4Cuts, and they said no.

453
00:22:22,382 --> 00:22:24,885
- Don't you think Tae-hoon seems…
- Yeah.

454
00:22:24,968 --> 00:22:26,428
…a bit drained by her?

455
00:22:26,511 --> 00:22:27,971
Why's he acting like that?

456
00:22:28,638 --> 00:22:30,098
Do you want some more?

457
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:32,434
- No, I'll do it.
- Were you really hungry?

458
00:22:32,517 --> 00:22:34,644
It's because it's tasty. I'm enjoying it.

459
00:22:34,728 --> 00:22:35,771
Hey, wait a second.

460
00:22:35,854 --> 00:22:38,398
Wait, hold on.
Why is he avoiding her eyes?

461
00:22:38,482 --> 00:22:41,068
- Ah…
- What do you think about that?

462
00:22:43,278 --> 00:22:44,946
- She's changed.
- Hey, wait. He's changed.

463
00:22:45,030 --> 00:22:46,990
- No, Kang Han-na has changed.
- No, look.

464
00:22:47,074 --> 00:22:49,785
- Tae-hoon wasn't like this before dinner.
- Right.

465
00:22:49,868 --> 00:22:52,496
Is he shy or something?
That can't be what's happening, right?

466
00:22:52,579 --> 00:22:53,914
He's not into her anymore.

467
00:22:55,749 --> 00:22:58,585
- He doesn't act the same.
- Hold on, hold on.

468
00:22:58,668 --> 00:23:01,755
I think Tae-hoon and Soo-hyun
got along so well at first

469
00:23:01,838 --> 00:23:05,217
because they had that giddy excitement
and were so friendly.

470
00:23:05,300 --> 00:23:07,636
- That's right.
- But now, Soo-hyun is…

471
00:23:07,719 --> 00:23:10,263
- She keeps coming.
- Her friend vibe is gone.

472
00:23:10,347 --> 00:23:13,016
She's giddy with a girlfriend vibe,
a lovey-dovey vibe.

473
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:16,019
So I think Tae-hoon's like,
"Whoa, okay, slow down, slow down."

474
00:23:16,103 --> 00:23:16,937
Yes.

475
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:18,730
And I also think it might be hard for him

476
00:23:18,814 --> 00:23:21,191
to kind of receive affection
and show affection.

477
00:23:21,274 --> 00:23:24,820
- All that in front of the other people.
- Especially given the situation.

478
00:23:25,904 --> 00:23:27,072
Were you hungry?

479
00:23:27,155 --> 00:23:28,865
No, I'm eating because I'm cold.

480
00:23:28,949 --> 00:23:30,700
- Because the weather's cold?
- Yeah.

481
00:23:32,202 --> 00:23:34,371
- You gonna drink that?
- No.

482
00:23:34,454 --> 00:23:36,289
To be fair, she doesn't let him breathe.

483
00:23:37,958 --> 00:23:39,543
He doesn't even talk to her.

484
00:23:40,585 --> 00:23:42,462
The weather's horrible too.

485
00:23:42,546 --> 00:23:44,423
- It's raining. Is it not?
- It is.

486
00:23:44,506 --> 00:23:46,216
- Unbelievable.
- Whoa.

487
00:23:48,135 --> 00:23:50,053
- Over there.
- Try his room.

488
00:23:50,137 --> 00:23:51,388
Yeah, try his room later.

489
00:23:51,972 --> 00:23:55,475
KIM JAE-SEO
CHOI HYUK-JOON

490
00:23:55,559 --> 00:23:56,852
How was it?

491
00:23:56,935 --> 00:24:00,355
I had a good conversation. It was good.

492
00:24:00,439 --> 00:24:02,149
What about you, bro?

493
00:24:02,232 --> 00:24:04,067
I had a good conversation too. Yeah.

494
00:24:04,151 --> 00:24:06,278
- Sounds like it was okay.
- Mmm.

495
00:24:06,361 --> 00:24:08,447
Okay, now for Tae-hoon's thoughts.

496
00:24:08,989 --> 00:24:11,533
I went with Soo-hyun
because she wanted to.

497
00:24:11,616 --> 00:24:12,742
Right.

498
00:24:14,077 --> 00:24:16,121
- But it wasn't great.
- Hmm.

499
00:24:16,204 --> 00:24:18,415
- Ah, see? I was right.
- Wow.

500
00:24:18,498 --> 00:24:22,210
I agreed to the date 'cause
we had good conversations, but, uh…

501
00:24:25,046 --> 00:24:26,089
I'm not sure yet.

502
00:24:26,173 --> 00:24:28,467
I've never felt
these kinds of emotions before.

503
00:24:29,092 --> 00:24:30,135
I'm just not sure.

504
00:24:30,218 --> 00:24:32,429
I do feel like I'm retreating a bit

505
00:24:32,512 --> 00:24:35,432
because I'm feeling a little overwhelmed.

506
00:24:35,515 --> 00:24:36,850
Ah, I wonder what happened.

507
00:24:36,933 --> 00:24:40,937
And I was a little bothered
by the plastic coffee bottle at dinner.

508
00:24:41,021 --> 00:24:42,355
- What?
- Why?

509
00:24:43,148 --> 00:24:45,734
I still had some Kanu coffee
at 11:00 p.m. yesterday.

510
00:24:45,817 --> 00:24:47,486
A single bottle lasts that long?

511
00:24:47,569 --> 00:24:49,237
I just keep adding water to it.

512
00:24:49,321 --> 00:24:50,989
You mean… Oh, you keep refilling it?

513
00:24:51,072 --> 00:24:53,825
Yeah, so it gets diluted,
but there's still coffee in there.

514
00:24:54,910 --> 00:24:56,828
When I get back, I'll do that too.

515
00:24:58,538 --> 00:25:00,790
Oh, he didn't like that she copied him.

516
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:04,711
She told me that she didn't
really drink coffee in the afternoon,

517
00:25:04,794 --> 00:25:07,005
so the fact that she was making
that kind of effort for me

518
00:25:07,088 --> 00:25:08,173
kind of overwhelmed me.

519
00:25:08,256 --> 00:25:10,342
Like, I wasn't quite sure
how to handle it.

520
00:25:10,425 --> 00:25:13,845
I think I'm starting at around 50%,

521
00:25:13,929 --> 00:25:17,599
but Soo-hyun's starting at,
like… 80% or 90%.

522
00:25:17,682 --> 00:25:20,519
So there's a bit of a gap between us.

523
00:25:23,188 --> 00:25:24,606
What a total mess.

524
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:26,691
I thought things would
finally get resolved today.

525
00:25:26,775 --> 00:25:28,068
- Seriously.
- Me too.

526
00:25:28,151 --> 00:25:30,028
Was it really that bad?

527
00:25:30,111 --> 00:25:32,906
I think it's like this. When it was
just the blueberry smoothie,

528
00:25:32,989 --> 00:25:35,617
they had lighthearted moments
whenever they ran into each other.

529
00:25:35,700 --> 00:25:36,535
Playful small talk.

530
00:25:36,618 --> 00:25:39,120
It was fun, they got along,
they were curious about each other.

531
00:25:39,204 --> 00:25:41,164
But from that moment they matched,

532
00:25:41,248 --> 00:25:43,542
they saw there was a certain degree
of mutual attraction.

533
00:25:43,625 --> 00:25:44,584
Yes.

534
00:25:44,668 --> 00:25:47,671
And then what happened
is that Soo-hyun came on too strongly.

535
00:25:47,754 --> 00:25:50,298
- That's right.
- Yeah. I'm not saying that was wrong.

536
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,050
- Right, right.
- Just different speeds.

537
00:25:52,133 --> 00:25:55,303
To be fair, though, you can't really
blame Soo-hyun for behaving that way.

538
00:25:55,387 --> 00:25:56,888
He made her blueberry smoothies,

539
00:25:56,972 --> 00:25:58,974
he checked out her books
in the 5 Minute Library.

540
00:25:59,057 --> 00:26:01,017
So, Soo-hyun's just like, "Oh, my gosh!"

541
00:26:01,101 --> 00:26:03,228
She's so happy that
she's totally opened her heart to him.

542
00:26:03,311 --> 00:26:05,105
And he also said
he wouldn't change his mind.

543
00:26:05,188 --> 00:26:07,482
She asked if he could change his mind,
he said, "No."

544
00:26:07,566 --> 00:26:09,901
- So true.
- Tae-hoon previously even asked about…

545
00:26:09,985 --> 00:26:12,654
- What was it? Return value?
- That was the funniest.

546
00:26:12,737 --> 00:26:14,948
He was so concerned
with getting the return value,

547
00:26:15,031 --> 00:26:17,534
but now that she's given it to him,
he's overwhelmed.

548
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:21,788
That's just so typical
of these eternal single kids, you know.

549
00:26:21,871 --> 00:26:23,665
"Kids," you say.

550
00:26:23,748 --> 00:26:26,084
As soon as someone asks something of them,

551
00:26:26,167 --> 00:26:27,669
they're overwhelmed by this and that.

552
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:30,088
- So true.
- All they keep trying to do is run away.

553
00:26:30,171 --> 00:26:32,716
I'm totally at a loss here,
just like last season.

554
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:36,761
- Oh, I think I'll have a milk one.
- Oh, just the girls.

555
00:26:36,845 --> 00:26:38,346
This is quite sweet.

556
00:26:38,430 --> 00:26:40,432
I'm the most curious
about your date today.

557
00:26:40,515 --> 00:26:42,017
- Same here.
- The most curious.

558
00:26:42,100 --> 00:26:43,560
- About me?
- Yeah.

559
00:26:43,643 --> 00:26:45,312
You're in the best mood out of everyone.

560
00:26:45,395 --> 00:26:46,813
- I am?
- Yeah.

561
00:26:46,896 --> 00:26:48,690
- Why aren't you happy?
- Yeah.

562
00:26:48,773 --> 00:26:50,400
Didn't you enjoy it, Su-ji?

563
00:26:51,067 --> 00:26:54,446
No, it was fun,
but it was just too comfortable.

564
00:26:54,529 --> 00:26:55,614
Oh, really?

565
00:26:55,697 --> 00:26:57,741
For Hyun-seo,
that's not a good sign at all.

566
00:26:57,824 --> 00:26:58,950
That's right.

567
00:26:59,034 --> 00:27:01,870
I thought that if I went on more dates,

568
00:27:01,953 --> 00:27:04,789
I'd gain more certainty
or come to a decision or something.

569
00:27:04,873 --> 00:27:08,251
But that hasn't been the case.
Nothing has changed at all.

570
00:27:08,335 --> 00:27:10,337
It's all nice and fun,

571
00:27:10,420 --> 00:27:12,339
but that's kind of where it ends.

572
00:27:12,422 --> 00:27:14,382
There's nothing beyond that.

573
00:27:17,469 --> 00:27:21,264
It was fun.
But I kind of thought I'd like him more

574
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:25,935
once we went on more dates
because Jung-yun's definitely my type.

575
00:27:26,519 --> 00:27:28,313
But that hasn't happened,

576
00:27:28,813 --> 00:27:32,108
So I'm a bit like,
"What's actually going on here?"

577
00:27:32,192 --> 00:27:34,027
"Should I talk to Hyuk-joon?"

578
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:37,906
But his story keeps changing,
so if I get the chance at some point,

579
00:27:37,989 --> 00:27:41,242
I'm gonna ask him
why he asked Han-ju out on a date

580
00:27:41,326 --> 00:27:43,119
after saying he found her boring.

581
00:27:43,203 --> 00:27:44,371
I'm genuinely curious.

582
00:27:44,454 --> 00:27:46,623
Why did he ask her out
if he thinks she's boring?

583
00:27:46,706 --> 00:27:47,791
Told you so.

584
00:27:48,291 --> 00:27:50,293
- She's leaning towards Hyuk-joon.
- Totally.

585
00:27:50,377 --> 00:27:52,003
She's leaning towards him,
but he chose Han-ju.

586
00:27:52,087 --> 00:27:53,546
- Yep.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

587
00:27:53,630 --> 00:27:55,757
I want to sit on the floor
because it's warm.

588
00:27:57,384 --> 00:28:00,220
There was a gift for me
at the Post Office today.

589
00:28:00,303 --> 00:28:02,514
- Really?
- But I don't know who left it for me.

590
00:28:02,597 --> 00:28:04,808
- There was no name?
- It wasn't signed?

591
00:28:04,891 --> 00:28:06,393
- No name.
- He thought it was from Han-ju.

592
00:28:06,476 --> 00:28:09,813
I thought I could detect it from the tone
of the letter that it was from Han-ju.

593
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:13,191
So that's what I thought, but when
I asked her, she said it wasn't her.

594
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:14,901
THIS AFTERNOON

595
00:28:14,984 --> 00:28:17,487
There was definitely a question
I wanted to ask you.

596
00:28:18,655 --> 00:28:20,532
Have you used your gift coupons yet?

597
00:28:21,700 --> 00:28:23,451
- Mm-mmm.
- Not yet?

598
00:28:23,535 --> 00:28:24,994
Hmm.

599
00:28:27,414 --> 00:28:28,748
Who's it from, then?

600
00:28:28,832 --> 00:28:31,793
So starting with the girls
you picked for the Three-way Date…

601
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:33,878
- Yeah, wouldn't it be one of them?
- Then Hyun-seo?

602
00:28:33,962 --> 00:28:37,173
I definitely don't think
it's Hyun-seo, though. Nope.

603
00:28:37,257 --> 00:28:38,258
Then who is it?

604
00:28:38,883 --> 00:28:40,343
I can think of one person.

605
00:28:40,885 --> 00:28:41,886
Who?

606
00:28:41,970 --> 00:28:44,431
- I think it was Jeong-eun.
- Why?

607
00:28:44,514 --> 00:28:46,683
Earlier, I think she said
she put things in both.

608
00:28:46,766 --> 00:28:48,643
- Put things in both?
- Yeah.

609
00:28:49,519 --> 00:28:51,855
I also got a letter from her this morning.
And a gift.

610
00:28:51,938 --> 00:28:52,772
THIS AFTERNOON

611
00:28:52,856 --> 00:28:54,566
At the Post Office. You wrote to someone?

612
00:28:54,649 --> 00:28:57,444
I wrote a letter for the first time.
My first time.

613
00:28:57,527 --> 00:28:59,112
Who did you write to?

614
00:28:59,195 --> 00:29:00,697
Who else?

615
00:29:00,780 --> 00:29:02,866
- Is there someone else you wrote to?
- There is.

616
00:29:03,908 --> 00:29:05,994
There is. But that doesn't mean

617
00:29:06,077 --> 00:29:08,246
I've changed my mind
about you or anything.

618
00:29:08,997 --> 00:29:12,751
It's just that there's someone
who still has a little more potential.

619
00:29:12,834 --> 00:29:13,835
Mmm.

620
00:29:14,669 --> 00:29:16,337
LAST NIGHT

621
00:29:16,421 --> 00:29:18,673
I'd been thinking of sending gifts

622
00:29:18,757 --> 00:29:21,301
once my list of potentials
had narrowed down a little,

623
00:29:21,384 --> 00:29:23,553
so I used the coupons as per that plan.

624
00:29:24,929 --> 00:29:27,515
I sent them to Jin-woo and Hyuk-joon.

625
00:29:29,225 --> 00:29:31,644
So the supplements were from Jeong-eun.

626
00:29:32,479 --> 00:29:33,646
Why to the both of us?

627
00:29:33,730 --> 00:29:34,731
I wouldn't know.

628
00:29:34,814 --> 00:29:36,858
- That makes no sense.
- I guess it was just…

629
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:40,236
Why would she give a gift to two people?
I really don't get that.

630
00:29:40,320 --> 00:29:42,071
"Why would she give a gift to two people?"

631
00:29:42,155 --> 00:29:43,948
Why do you go on dates with everyone?

632
00:29:45,450 --> 00:29:47,660
- He has a point.
- Why don't you tell me, Hyuk-joon?

633
00:29:47,744 --> 00:29:48,995
- Great point.
- Please do!

634
00:29:49,078 --> 00:29:52,290
Well, if Jin-woo and Hyuk-joon
are her first and second choices,

635
00:29:52,373 --> 00:29:53,875
why shouldn't she give them both a gift?

636
00:29:53,958 --> 00:29:57,003
Because they were her first and second
choices for the Three-way Date too.

637
00:29:57,086 --> 00:29:59,214
See, it's easy to fall
into the double standards trap.

638
00:29:59,297 --> 00:30:01,758
- So true.
- Man, he's got some nerves, that one.

639
00:30:01,841 --> 00:30:06,095
But I think she said
she wrote to both of us.

640
00:30:07,388 --> 00:30:09,974
Both of you? Well, why not, I guess.

641
00:30:10,975 --> 00:30:13,853
I wouldn't know
since I've never gotten one.

642
00:30:13,937 --> 00:30:15,188
Jae-seo hasn't.

643
00:30:15,271 --> 00:30:17,607
Anyway, mine wasn't signed. Was yours?

644
00:30:17,690 --> 00:30:20,527
No, there was no name anywhere,
just the gift and the letter.

645
00:30:20,610 --> 00:30:23,154
Well, since she told you
she wrote to both of you,

646
00:30:23,238 --> 00:30:25,156
I don't think her intention
was to hide it.

647
00:30:25,865 --> 00:30:29,077
But I really don't get
why she would give a gift

648
00:30:29,160 --> 00:30:31,079
to two guys at the same time, though.

649
00:30:31,162 --> 00:30:33,122
Right. And adding a gift too is a little…

650
00:30:33,206 --> 00:30:35,291
Exactly. I mean,
writing a letter's one thing,

651
00:30:35,375 --> 00:30:37,502
but giving a gift
to two people baffles me.

652
00:30:37,585 --> 00:30:39,045
Were the two gifts different?

653
00:30:39,128 --> 00:30:40,338
Mine's a good-luck fish.

654
00:30:40,421 --> 00:30:42,131
So she gave you what you wanted.

655
00:30:42,215 --> 00:30:43,258
I got supplements.

656
00:30:45,176 --> 00:30:47,595
So Jin-woo thinks it was Jeong-eun
because she told him

657
00:30:47,679 --> 00:30:49,472
she'd sent a gift to two people.

658
00:30:49,556 --> 00:30:52,809
And for me,
I have a bit of a problem with that.

659
00:30:52,892 --> 00:30:57,313
Especially giving a letter and a gift
to two different guys on the same day

660
00:30:57,397 --> 00:30:59,274
at the same time makes no sense.

661
00:30:59,983 --> 00:31:03,862
Isn't a gift something
you give someone you really like?

662
00:31:03,945 --> 00:31:05,613
So I was like, "What is this?"

663
00:31:05,697 --> 00:31:08,700
"Why is she going around bragging
that she gave gifts to two guys?"

664
00:31:08,783 --> 00:31:10,201
She never bragged.

665
00:31:10,285 --> 00:31:12,078
I don't know if I should put it like this,

666
00:31:12,161 --> 00:31:14,956
but I'd say
she's been crossed off my list.

667
00:31:15,748 --> 00:31:16,958
What?

668
00:31:17,041 --> 00:31:18,918
Oops. Ah.

669
00:31:19,544 --> 00:31:20,670
"Crossed off my list"?

670
00:31:21,963 --> 00:31:23,298
Crossed off for giving two gifts.

671
00:31:23,381 --> 00:31:25,758
Do you think Hyuk-joon's been
possessed by something here?

672
00:31:25,842 --> 00:31:26,718
Possessed?

673
00:31:26,801 --> 00:31:28,386
I think he's possessed by something.

674
00:31:28,469 --> 00:31:29,846
Maybe he's possessed.

675
00:31:29,929 --> 00:31:33,600
Jeong-eun didn't brag about anything.
And I don't think Jin-woo did either.

676
00:31:33,683 --> 00:31:36,561
In fact, Jeong-eun only told Jin-woo that
because he asked her the question.

677
00:31:36,644 --> 00:31:37,937
- Right.
- Exactly.

678
00:31:38,021 --> 00:31:41,441
It seems a gift carries a much bigger
significance for Hyuk-joon than a date.

679
00:31:41,524 --> 00:31:42,859
Oh, than a date?

680
00:31:42,942 --> 00:31:45,194
- A date is just a date.
- A date is just, you know, talking.

681
00:31:45,278 --> 00:31:47,363
When it comes to the nice room
or whatever it's called,

682
00:31:47,447 --> 00:31:48,865
he can take whoever he wants.

683
00:31:48,948 --> 00:31:51,534
Taking this girl, then that girl,
all of that's fine, but…

684
00:31:51,618 --> 00:31:53,286
- But gifts…
- "A gift? How could you?"

685
00:31:53,369 --> 00:31:54,787
Maybe that's how he thinks.

686
00:31:54,871 --> 00:31:57,957
Perhaps he thinks gifts are more important
because they're really secretive?

687
00:31:58,041 --> 00:32:00,877
He thought it was a definitive declaration
of one's feelings like it's final.

688
00:32:00,960 --> 00:32:01,836
That's right.

689
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:05,173
Do you, like…
Do you have something like a hierarchy?

690
00:32:05,256 --> 00:32:07,550
Kind of like a hierarchy
of your interest level?

691
00:32:07,634 --> 00:32:08,635
Anything like that yet?

692
00:32:08,718 --> 00:32:10,428
Han-ju was his first choice.

693
00:32:10,511 --> 00:32:13,473
The supplements I got today were
actually really significant to me.

694
00:32:13,556 --> 00:32:16,100
- I thought it was from Han-ju, so…
- Oh. You didn't know who it was from.

695
00:32:16,184 --> 00:32:17,644
Yeah, but it turned out not to be her.

696
00:32:17,727 --> 00:32:20,313
It was sweet, though,
to give you supplements.

697
00:32:20,396 --> 00:32:24,067
Even so, I'm disillusioned by the fact
that she gave gifts to the both of us.

698
00:32:24,150 --> 00:32:27,654
- True. If she'd given only you a gift…
- From my point of view, I was played.

699
00:32:27,737 --> 00:32:29,989
- Right. I guess.
- Yeah. So…

700
00:32:30,073 --> 00:32:32,075
- What are you going to say today?
- My top pick?

701
00:32:32,158 --> 00:32:34,535
Well, I'm not sure who
my top pick is right now.

702
00:32:34,619 --> 00:32:36,496
I'm not even sure about Hyun-seo
right now.

703
00:32:36,579 --> 00:32:40,583
Because I've already given her a gift
and a letter and everything.

704
00:32:40,667 --> 00:32:41,584
Hmm.

705
00:32:42,418 --> 00:32:45,338
Mmm,
I'm currently just trying to figure out

706
00:32:46,214 --> 00:32:48,132
what it is exactly that I'm feeling.

707
00:32:48,967 --> 00:32:51,636
This time,
I'm really overwhelmed with thoughts.

708
00:32:51,719 --> 00:32:56,808
The supplements and the letter felt
so sincere to me, you know?

709
00:32:56,891 --> 00:32:58,601
The letter was really long too.

710
00:32:59,310 --> 00:33:03,272
I'd started to like Han-ju more
because I was so moved by it,

711
00:33:03,773 --> 00:33:06,901
so finding out that it wasn't her
after all made me wonder

712
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:11,447
if all the emotional investment
I'd made today had been misguided,

713
00:33:11,531 --> 00:33:13,533
and that troubled me a lot.

714
00:33:13,616 --> 00:33:15,827
So he liked her
because she gave him a gift?

715
00:33:15,910 --> 00:33:17,787
But you're the one
who got your wires crossed!

716
00:33:17,870 --> 00:33:21,416
- Gifts are really a big deal to Hyuk-joon.
- Ugh, so frustrating.

717
00:33:21,499 --> 00:33:23,084
And also…

718
00:33:25,878 --> 00:33:28,256
Well, I'm only human
at the end of the day,

719
00:33:29,132 --> 00:33:33,469
so I'd held out some hope
that if I went off on a date

720
00:33:33,553 --> 00:33:35,304
with someone else,

721
00:33:35,388 --> 00:33:37,849
Hyun-seo would get concerned,

722
00:33:37,932 --> 00:33:41,227
and perhaps she would think
of writing me a letter

723
00:33:41,310 --> 00:33:42,979
or something like that.

724
00:33:43,604 --> 00:33:47,817
So I did stop by the Post Office
as soon as I got back.

725
00:33:47,900 --> 00:33:49,193
So pathetic.

726
00:33:49,277 --> 00:33:50,862
What is he even talking about?

727
00:33:50,945 --> 00:33:53,489
That's not pathetic.
That's totally arrogant.

728
00:33:53,573 --> 00:33:56,242
Exactly. He didn't write her a letter
when he went on his date,

729
00:33:56,325 --> 00:33:58,745
but he was hoping she'd write him one
while he was gone. That's a bit…

730
00:33:58,828 --> 00:34:01,080
- What's with this guy?
- Oh, boy.

731
00:34:01,164 --> 00:34:04,584
2 HOURS AGO

732
00:34:13,926 --> 00:34:16,596
I stopped by the Post Office,
but there was nothing there.

733
00:34:19,557 --> 00:34:21,934
I really, really like Hyun-seo.

734
00:34:22,018 --> 00:34:23,644
Like, a lot. I can't…

735
00:34:23,728 --> 00:34:25,855
I wish I could,
but I can't let go of her yet

736
00:34:25,938 --> 00:34:27,482
because I can't just ignore fate.

737
00:34:27,565 --> 00:34:31,319
Because the situation was so crazy.

738
00:34:31,402 --> 00:34:33,654
We were just drawing names at random.

739
00:34:33,738 --> 00:34:36,365
And the scissors too.
Literally, all the participants,

740
00:34:36,449 --> 00:34:39,285
both male and female,
were curious about that item.

741
00:34:39,368 --> 00:34:42,497
This kind of thing
doesn't just happen for no reason,

742
00:34:42,580 --> 00:34:45,166
so it's not something
I can let go of easily.

743
00:34:45,249 --> 00:34:49,837
So if Hyun-seo could at one point
just make a little more effort,

744
00:34:49,921 --> 00:34:52,298
even just the tiniest,
tiniest bit of effort--

745
00:34:52,381 --> 00:34:53,299
I mean, look at me.

746
00:34:53,382 --> 00:34:56,636
I ran to the box of gifts on day two
so I could send her one.

747
00:34:56,719 --> 00:34:58,471
And I also wrote a heartfelt letter.

748
00:34:58,554 --> 00:35:02,475
I wrote it as fast as I could,
asking myself, "Does she need anything?"

749
00:35:02,558 --> 00:35:04,102
Seriously, all my attention was on her.

750
00:35:04,185 --> 00:35:06,062
He still has feelings for Hyun-seo.

751
00:35:06,145 --> 00:35:07,855
Oh, he can't let go of fate.

752
00:35:08,397 --> 00:35:10,399
- Are your shoes comfortable?
- Yeah, they're fine.

753
00:35:11,234 --> 00:35:14,028
Let me get the seat belt. Right here.

754
00:35:14,862 --> 00:35:16,280
- I got it.
- The seat belt?

755
00:35:16,364 --> 00:35:17,949
- Oh, thank you.
- Oh, there you go.

756
00:35:20,952 --> 00:35:23,204
- There's something on your lip.
- Oh, really?

757
00:35:23,287 --> 00:35:24,288
Yeah.

758
00:35:27,583 --> 00:35:29,377
Here. Mmm. A little bit lower.

759
00:35:30,586 --> 00:35:32,338
- Yeah, you're good.
- Thank you.

760
00:35:32,421 --> 00:35:34,340
I really made a lot of effort.

761
00:35:34,924 --> 00:35:37,426
But if she showed me a quarter,

762
00:35:37,927 --> 00:35:41,389
even just an eighth of the effort I made,

763
00:35:42,140 --> 00:35:43,641
I think I'd come around.

764
00:35:44,976 --> 00:35:47,186
I think it could increase, yes.

765
00:35:47,687 --> 00:35:49,647
But Hyun-seo really expressed
her feelings.

766
00:35:49,730 --> 00:35:51,774
Remember the whole
"I'll tear you to shreds" thing?

767
00:35:51,858 --> 00:35:54,193
Do you think it's because
she hasn't given him a gift?

768
00:35:54,277 --> 00:35:55,820
"I gave her a tumbler,

769
00:35:55,903 --> 00:35:58,322
but every time I go to the Post Office
and check my mailbox,

770
00:35:58,406 --> 00:35:59,615
there's no gift there."

771
00:35:59,699 --> 00:36:00,658
Oh, yes!

772
00:36:00,741 --> 00:36:04,120
There are five love languages, you know?
Maybe his is gifts.

773
00:36:04,745 --> 00:36:08,541
"Yeah, I don't think
we're very compatible, the two of us."

774
00:36:08,624 --> 00:36:09,876
"Let's just break up."

775
00:36:09,959 --> 00:36:11,752
"Why didn't you give me
a gift for our anniversary?"

776
00:36:13,004 --> 00:36:15,798
- "Why is there no gift?"
- That's basically what he's doing.

777
00:36:15,882 --> 00:36:19,635
Hyuk-joon told me he was kept
on the hook by his first love,

778
00:36:19,719 --> 00:36:22,054
and it left him deeply, deeply scarred.

779
00:36:22,138 --> 00:36:23,222
Oh, that's right.

780
00:36:23,306 --> 00:36:25,474
That's why I think
he set himself a benchmark,

781
00:36:25,558 --> 00:36:28,436
something very thoroughly detailed
and concrete in his mind.

782
00:36:28,519 --> 00:36:30,563
- And like Eun-ji said earlier…
- Yes.

783
00:36:30,646 --> 00:36:33,149
…since he considers gifts
to be something very secretive,

784
00:36:33,232 --> 00:36:35,318
that became, in turn,
his absolute standard.

785
00:36:35,401 --> 00:36:37,195
Oh, I can see how that could happen.

786
00:36:37,278 --> 00:36:41,532
However, since he was only acting
according to his own standards,

787
00:36:41,616 --> 00:36:43,284
it was actually pretty selfish.

788
00:36:43,367 --> 00:36:46,704
I actually think Hyuk-joon has liked
Hyun-seo since the beginning,

789
00:36:46,787 --> 00:36:48,873
and all along, but also,

790
00:36:48,956 --> 00:36:52,335
he felt she wasn't reciprocating with
the same amount of expression…

791
00:36:52,418 --> 00:36:53,878
- Not reciprocating?
- He was hurt.

792
00:36:53,961 --> 00:36:55,963
So he went on those other dates
on purpose?

793
00:36:56,047 --> 00:36:58,466
Wouldn't that explain
why he did those strange things?

794
00:37:19,028 --> 00:37:20,279
Why is he alone?

795
00:37:20,363 --> 00:37:22,240
- Su-ji? It's Su-ji?
- It's Su-ji.

796
00:37:25,243 --> 00:37:26,619
What are you doing here alone?

797
00:37:26,702 --> 00:37:28,996
Oh, I'm eating chocolate.

798
00:37:29,080 --> 00:37:30,373
That's mine.

799
00:37:30,456 --> 00:37:32,792
I'm kidding. Go for it. Go on, go on.

800
00:37:33,584 --> 00:37:36,254
- It's the only chocolate I ate.
- That's all right. Have more.

801
00:37:36,337 --> 00:37:39,715
There's more chocolate over there.
I noticed you really like chocolate.

802
00:37:40,383 --> 00:37:43,302
I have a feeling Su-ji's about to ask him
what she's been curious about.

803
00:37:43,386 --> 00:37:44,637
She should ask him.

804
00:37:47,181 --> 00:37:48,182
What's up?

805
00:37:49,809 --> 00:37:51,769
No, there's something
I'm kind of curious about.

806
00:37:51,852 --> 00:37:53,437
- Me? What is it?
- Yeah.

807
00:37:53,521 --> 00:37:57,316
You know yesterday
when we were having a conversation?

808
00:37:57,400 --> 00:37:58,401
Mm-hmm.

809
00:37:58,484 --> 00:38:01,445
You told me that
your Three-way Date had been boring.

810
00:38:01,529 --> 00:38:03,572
That it had been uncomfortable.

811
00:38:05,658 --> 00:38:06,993
How was your date today?

812
00:38:07,076 --> 00:38:07,910
LAST NIGHT

813
00:38:07,994 --> 00:38:09,620
The date today…

814
00:38:09,704 --> 00:38:13,416
The Three-way Date was
a little awkward and uncomfortable.

815
00:38:13,499 --> 00:38:14,834
Oh, I can see that.

816
00:38:14,917 --> 00:38:16,210
The one with Han-ju.

817
00:38:18,004 --> 00:38:20,256
Uncomfortable. I guess I thought

818
00:38:20,339 --> 00:38:22,925
you meant you found it boring
when you said it was uncomfortable.

819
00:38:23,009 --> 00:38:23,968
I'm sorry.

820
00:38:24,051 --> 00:38:26,971
I was wondering why you had
picked Han-ju when you told me

821
00:38:27,054 --> 00:38:29,890
you found it uncomfortable
and just kind of boring,

822
00:38:29,974 --> 00:38:31,976
but I misunderstood.

823
00:38:32,059 --> 00:38:34,312
Yeah, I think you did misunderstand.

824
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:36,355
That's why I came here
right away to ask you.

825
00:38:36,439 --> 00:38:39,400
Yeah, I always want to check
if I'm misunderstanding something.

826
00:38:39,483 --> 00:38:41,444
That's what you were curious about? Why?

827
00:38:41,527 --> 00:38:43,738
Yeah, I came here to ask you
because I was curious.

828
00:38:44,822 --> 00:38:46,115
Yeah. I see.

829
00:38:46,198 --> 00:38:48,117
- It was uncomfortable.
- I understand perfectly now.

830
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:51,662
She thought he meant his date
with Han-ju had been boring.

831
00:38:51,746 --> 00:38:54,373
She thought he went on a date
with someone he had no interest in.

832
00:38:54,457 --> 00:38:55,499
Yeah.

833
00:38:55,583 --> 00:38:56,667
I kind of…

834
00:38:57,918 --> 00:39:00,379
have so much going on in my head now.

835
00:39:09,638 --> 00:39:11,682
I thought you had a good date today.

836
00:39:11,766 --> 00:39:13,059
I did, yes.

837
00:39:13,768 --> 00:39:15,770
Is there something you can't tell me?

838
00:39:17,938 --> 00:39:20,316
- I don't think I can tell you everything.
- Why not?

839
00:39:22,485 --> 00:39:23,694
Mmm…

840
00:39:29,533 --> 00:39:33,287
Wouldn't it be weird for me to talk
about what's going on with another guy

841
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:35,664
when I'm also still
kind of interested in you?

842
00:39:42,338 --> 00:39:43,756
Oh, I get what you mean.

843
00:39:43,839 --> 00:39:44,924
Right, right.

844
00:39:47,385 --> 00:39:49,845
- Today's been confusing for me too.
- Was it?

845
00:39:49,929 --> 00:39:53,849
Yeah. Like you said,
I can't go into too much detail, but…

846
00:39:57,186 --> 00:39:58,896
Wow, this is weird.

847
00:39:59,980 --> 00:40:01,982
- Gosh.
- It's a weird vibe.

848
00:40:05,486 --> 00:40:08,447
Hey, if you do pottery,
do you make rings and stuff yourself too?

849
00:40:08,531 --> 00:40:10,699
I can. Why? Do you want to try?

850
00:40:10,783 --> 00:40:13,994
I was curious about
what you did in your job.

851
00:40:14,787 --> 00:40:16,705
Hmm.

852
00:40:16,789 --> 00:40:20,835
My mom's been a huge influence on me,
especially when it comes to pottery.

853
00:40:20,918 --> 00:40:25,131
But my aunt loves tableware too and used
to visit tableware factories all the time.

854
00:40:25,214 --> 00:40:28,426
So I'm practically
my aunt's third daughter.

855
00:40:29,677 --> 00:40:31,470
Your family really dotes on you.

856
00:40:32,596 --> 00:40:34,056
- Yeah?
- It seems like it.

857
00:40:34,807 --> 00:40:39,186
Thank you. Although,
I'm not sure what you mean by that.

858
00:40:39,812 --> 00:40:40,980
It's a positive thing.

859
00:40:41,063 --> 00:40:43,274
You seem like a person
who's loved by their family.

860
00:40:45,818 --> 00:40:46,902
Oh, really?

861
00:40:49,989 --> 00:40:52,074
There are no sharp edges to you.

862
00:40:52,158 --> 00:40:55,244
Is it my birthday today?
So many compliments.

863
00:40:55,911 --> 00:40:58,164
It just came up in conversation,
that's all.

864
00:40:58,247 --> 00:40:59,457
- Well, thank you.
- Sure.

865
00:40:59,540 --> 00:41:01,167
I kind of have a weakness for compliments.

866
00:41:01,250 --> 00:41:02,334
- Oh, do you?
- Yeah.

867
00:41:02,418 --> 00:41:05,588
Oh, you said that yesterday too,
when I mentioned you were pretty.

868
00:41:05,671 --> 00:41:09,049
Thanks! And then randomly looking away.

869
00:41:10,342 --> 00:41:11,552
Oh, she likes that.

870
00:41:12,178 --> 00:41:13,512
- Let's get it.
- Yeah.

871
00:41:13,596 --> 00:41:15,097
Both of us. Let's do our best.

872
00:41:15,181 --> 00:41:16,765
- Your hand's so warm.
- Oh, look.

873
00:41:16,849 --> 00:41:19,018
I thought you were like the sun.

874
00:41:19,101 --> 00:41:22,062
It's my secret trick. This one's
really cold, and this one's really warm.

875
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:23,606
Secret trick?

876
00:41:27,693 --> 00:41:30,488
Have you ever seen Su-ji high-five anyone?

877
00:41:30,571 --> 00:41:32,990
- She doesn't.
- She does it so naturally with Hyuk-joon.

878
00:41:33,073 --> 00:41:35,034
- She keeps doing it.
- She shakes hands with him too.

879
00:41:35,117 --> 00:41:36,660
And she grabs on to everything he says.

880
00:41:36,744 --> 00:41:38,704
That's why their conversations
last so long.

881
00:41:40,039 --> 00:41:41,207
Oh, hello.

882
00:41:46,045 --> 00:41:47,046
Oh, dear.

883
00:41:47,129 --> 00:41:49,256
She's seen them.

884
00:41:49,340 --> 00:41:50,549
Oh, boy.

885
00:41:53,302 --> 00:41:55,804
Okay. Oh, that's right.

886
00:41:55,888 --> 00:41:59,683
Hey, you know when I said that thing
about guys being weeded out?

887
00:41:59,767 --> 00:42:01,352
You didn't take it the wrong way, did you?

888
00:42:01,435 --> 00:42:02,811
- Why do you ask?
- Well…

889
00:42:02,895 --> 00:42:05,356
Hey, Stop talking nonsense.
Get out of here. Go.

890
00:42:05,439 --> 00:42:07,608
Jae-seo heard you say the word

891
00:42:07,691 --> 00:42:12,279
and asked me if I had somehow
messed up in any way with you.

892
00:42:12,363 --> 00:42:13,197
Oh.

893
00:42:13,280 --> 00:42:17,117
We were just talking,
and I said we should make a toast.

894
00:42:17,201 --> 00:42:20,746
And he asked me out of concern,
"Did you mess up with Hyun-seo?"

895
00:42:20,829 --> 00:42:24,750
I saw Hyuk-joon and Su-ji talking
together, just the two of them,

896
00:42:24,833 --> 00:42:27,878
so I thought maybe I should go over, but…

897
00:42:27,962 --> 00:42:30,673
Hyun-seo's looking in there,
but he keeps rambling to her.

898
00:42:32,007 --> 00:42:33,509
Let's go inside.

899
00:42:33,592 --> 00:42:36,345
Oh, uh, looks like they're
still having a serious conversation.

900
00:42:36,428 --> 00:42:38,389
- Oh, really?
- Yeah. This could be a while.

901
00:42:38,472 --> 00:42:40,307
But she knows, Hyuk-joon.

902
00:42:40,391 --> 00:42:41,475
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

903
00:42:41,559 --> 00:42:43,269
Well, I guess it can't be helped.

904
00:42:43,352 --> 00:42:44,770
Ugh…

905
00:42:44,853 --> 00:42:49,275
It almost felt
like Tae-hoon was trying to stop me.

906
00:42:49,358 --> 00:42:52,695
I felt like he kept blocking my path.
So I thought,

907
00:42:52,778 --> 00:42:55,114
"Oh, I guess tonight's the night
Su-ji and Hyuk-joon

908
00:42:55,197 --> 00:42:58,701
must be having
a really important conversation."

909
00:42:58,784 --> 00:43:02,246
I mean, Su-ji is interested in Hyuk-joon.

910
00:43:03,747 --> 00:43:04,873
So,

911
00:43:05,958 --> 00:43:09,169
I walked around near the Lounge,
thinking they might be done at some point,

912
00:43:09,253 --> 00:43:11,338
but they continued talking
for quite a while.

913
00:43:11,422 --> 00:43:13,132
She continued pacing around like that.

914
00:43:13,215 --> 00:43:15,634
Because it's been so long
since the two of them talked.

915
00:43:15,718 --> 00:43:18,012
I had something to ask,
but I guess I can't.

916
00:43:18,637 --> 00:43:20,014
- Ask who?
- Hyuk-joon.

917
00:43:20,097 --> 00:43:21,432
Hyuk-joon?

918
00:43:21,515 --> 00:43:23,100
Hey, I can wait with you.

919
00:43:23,183 --> 00:43:25,394
But waiting for him is kind of weird too.

920
00:43:25,477 --> 00:43:26,645
Yeah?

921
00:43:26,729 --> 00:43:28,355
- Let's go.
- All right.

922
00:43:28,439 --> 00:43:31,066
I mean, it's not like I can
change his decision anyway.

923
00:43:31,150 --> 00:43:33,444
Yeah, let's see what happens tomorrow.

924
00:43:37,281 --> 00:43:40,034
It's true, Hyuk-joon is my first choice,

925
00:43:40,117 --> 00:43:41,952
but I just felt unsettled.

926
00:43:43,162 --> 00:43:46,081
Wow, you guys, this is so frustrating.

927
00:43:46,165 --> 00:43:47,374
KIM SOO-HYUN
JEON SEO-YOON

928
00:43:47,458 --> 00:43:50,085
- Oh, I don't know.
- I'm feeling unsettled again.

929
00:43:51,003 --> 00:43:53,047
- Are they still talking?
- I don't know.

930
00:43:54,423 --> 00:43:59,428
But I think he might go
on a date with Su-ji again tomorrow.

931
00:44:02,222 --> 00:44:03,891
Then it'll really be over.

932
00:44:03,974 --> 00:44:05,434
- You really think?
- Yeah.

933
00:44:10,856 --> 00:44:12,024
Oh…

934
00:44:13,942 --> 00:44:17,279
To be honest, my feelings for him,

935
00:44:17,363 --> 00:44:19,448
my interest isn't the same as before.

936
00:44:20,491 --> 00:44:24,078
He was having a serious conversation
with Su-ji when we were in the Noraebang,

937
00:44:24,161 --> 00:44:25,537
and it lasted a while.

938
00:44:26,372 --> 00:44:28,040
I just thought, "Oh, okay,"

939
00:44:28,123 --> 00:44:31,210
because now Hyuk-joon
is Su-ji's second choice.

940
00:44:31,293 --> 00:44:35,464
But then today, Su-ji said she didn't
enjoy her date with Jung-yun earlier,

941
00:44:35,547 --> 00:44:39,259
so I guess now she wants to go on a date
with Hyuk-joon tomorrow.

942
00:44:39,802 --> 00:44:43,430
But if Hyuk-joon really does go
on a date with Su-ji tomorrow,

943
00:44:43,514 --> 00:44:45,933
I'll have to assume
he no longer has feelings for me.

944
00:44:46,016 --> 00:44:47,559
Hmm.

945
00:44:47,643 --> 00:44:49,269
Of course he doesn't have feelings for me.

946
00:44:49,353 --> 00:44:51,689
Otherwise, why go on a date
with four other girls?

947
00:44:51,772 --> 00:44:53,399
- That's true.
- Logically speaking.

948
00:44:54,024 --> 00:44:55,401
I'm not happy with him.

949
00:44:56,652 --> 00:44:57,528
Are you angry?

950
00:44:57,611 --> 00:44:59,613
- I'm not really angry.
- You're just annoyed?

951
00:44:59,697 --> 00:45:01,073
More frustrated. Yeah.

952
00:45:03,117 --> 00:45:04,785
I don't know what he's thinking.

953
00:45:04,868 --> 00:45:05,869
Right.

954
00:45:10,582 --> 00:45:12,626
- Oh, hold on.
- Oh, I'm hot.

955
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:15,003
This is the first time
I'm seeing her get worked up.

956
00:45:15,087 --> 00:45:16,088
This is frustrating.

957
00:45:16,171 --> 00:45:19,049
- I'm getting worked up.
- Hey, Hyuk-joon, what an achievement.

958
00:45:19,133 --> 00:45:20,843
This really is an achievement.

959
00:45:20,926 --> 00:45:22,344
I didn't know you could get all worked up.

960
00:45:22,428 --> 00:45:25,806
You're the only person who's pissed off
our resident Mother Teresa.

961
00:45:25,889 --> 00:45:27,975
- What a feat.
- It really is.

962
00:45:28,058 --> 00:45:30,227
Hyuk-joon, you really are something.

963
00:45:30,310 --> 00:45:33,021
But now if he goes on a date with Su-ji,
Hyun-seo will dump him,

964
00:45:33,105 --> 00:45:36,316
and if he goes with Hyun-seo,
then Su-ji will likely dump him as well.

965
00:45:36,400 --> 00:45:37,359
I think so.

966
00:45:37,443 --> 00:45:39,278
I think Hyuk-joon has really
reached the point

967
00:45:39,361 --> 00:45:40,779
where he has to make a decision.

968
00:45:40,863 --> 00:45:41,780
Now's the time.

969
00:45:41,864 --> 00:45:44,408
That's why I was trying
to talk to him today.

970
00:45:44,491 --> 00:45:46,368
- Right.
- To find out what he was thinking.

971
00:45:46,452 --> 00:45:49,246
- Right.
- But he talked to Su-ji for so long.

972
00:45:49,329 --> 00:45:52,040
Yeah, he didn't get a chance
to talk to Hyun-seo at all.

973
00:45:52,124 --> 00:45:54,168
So is he talking with Su-ji now?

974
00:45:54,251 --> 00:45:56,003
I don't know.
I haven't been to the Lounge.

975
00:45:56,795 --> 00:46:00,841
But it felt like Tae-hoon was deliberately
preventing me from going in.

976
00:46:02,551 --> 00:46:06,138
Look, he suddenly started talking to me,
when he never talks to me.

977
00:46:07,139 --> 00:46:10,058
Wow, there's the bro code. Oh, my gosh.

978
00:46:10,142 --> 00:46:12,144
No, look. I was outside the Noraebang,

979
00:46:12,227 --> 00:46:14,897
about to do a lap to go to the Lounge,

980
00:46:14,980 --> 00:46:19,026
and out of nowhere, he blocked my path
and started to talk to me, saying,

981
00:46:19,109 --> 00:46:21,069
"Hey, you know, yesterday,
I said that thing

982
00:46:21,153 --> 00:46:23,363
about you guys being weeded out
and offended you?"

983
00:46:23,447 --> 00:46:25,491
So I said, "Don't worry about it,"
and started going in,

984
00:46:25,574 --> 00:46:28,452
but he wouldn't leave my side
and kept going, "No, but…"

985
00:46:28,535 --> 00:46:31,830
And when I looked toward the Lounge,
he was like, "Oh, I heard from Jae-seo."

986
00:46:31,914 --> 00:46:35,876
It kind of made me feel like he was
trying to stop me from going in.

987
00:46:35,959 --> 00:46:38,420
Did he really think you wouldn't
see them if he stopped you?

988
00:46:38,504 --> 00:46:40,506
- Yeah.
- I was like, "What's up with him?"

989
00:46:41,548 --> 00:46:43,258
It ticked me off even more.

990
00:46:43,342 --> 00:46:46,386
I mean, what could they be talking about
for him to act like this?

991
00:46:47,429 --> 00:46:49,848
I mean, maybe it's nothing special, but…

992
00:46:50,432 --> 00:46:52,476
Ugh, I'm so frustrated.

993
00:46:54,019 --> 00:46:56,271
It's clear Hyun-seo still likes Hyuk-joon.

994
00:46:56,355 --> 00:46:59,066
You know those people who don't break up
when everyone's telling them to?

995
00:46:59,149 --> 00:47:01,235
- Absolutely.
- That's what this feels like.

996
00:47:01,318 --> 00:47:04,404
But I think Hyuk-joon also likes Hyun-seo,
based on what he says.

997
00:47:04,488 --> 00:47:06,949
But I wish he could be
a little more certain.

998
00:47:07,032 --> 00:47:09,660
I get that he's confused
about his feelings,

999
00:47:09,743 --> 00:47:13,080
but for the sake of others, he should
make up his mind sooner than later.

1000
00:47:13,163 --> 00:47:14,957
- I think he needs to.
- Totally.

1001
00:47:17,793 --> 00:47:19,211
It's Tae-hoon.

1002
00:47:19,294 --> 00:47:21,213
- Hi.
- Where've you been?

1003
00:47:21,296 --> 00:47:22,631
- Me?
- Seriously, where?

1004
00:47:22,714 --> 00:47:24,550
I was just playing bystander today.

1005
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:26,969
- What's "playing bystander"?
- What do you mean?

1006
00:47:27,052 --> 00:47:31,098
People were in deep conversation, and then
the Noraebang was empty, so I came here.

1007
00:47:31,181 --> 00:47:35,310
I wandered around, went to the Lounge,
saw what was going on there.

1008
00:47:35,394 --> 00:47:37,020
- Who's in the Lounge?
- Who's in the Lounge?

1009
00:47:37,104 --> 00:47:38,689
Huh? Hyuk-joon and Su-ji.

1010
00:47:38,772 --> 00:47:40,315
- They're still talking?
- Yeah.

1011
00:47:40,399 --> 00:47:41,775
It's been a long time.

1012
00:47:42,442 --> 00:47:43,443
Oh, really?

1013
00:47:43,527 --> 00:47:46,113
I guess Jung-yun will also
wonder what's going on.

1014
00:47:46,780 --> 00:47:48,866
- I was waiting to talk to him.
- Really?

1015
00:47:48,949 --> 00:47:52,870
Yeah, but Su-ji just wouldn't come out.
It's been a real long time.

1016
00:47:52,953 --> 00:47:54,705
She must have a lot to talk about.

1017
00:47:55,497 --> 00:47:56,623
She does.

1018
00:47:58,125 --> 00:47:59,543
Oh, again?

1019
00:48:00,669 --> 00:48:05,507
But I think, Su-ji… for her, they're
pretty equal. Jung-yun and Hyuk-joon.

1020
00:48:06,174 --> 00:48:07,384
I guess that could be right.

1021
00:48:08,719 --> 00:48:12,014
No, she told me from the start
that the gap between us isn't big.

1022
00:48:12,097 --> 00:48:13,390
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1023
00:48:13,473 --> 00:48:15,392
- What?
- It does look like you're equal.

1024
00:48:15,475 --> 00:48:16,476
Oh, really?

1025
00:48:17,269 --> 00:48:20,147
- Doesn't that upset you?
- Oh, Tae-hoon, come on.

1026
00:48:20,230 --> 00:48:21,565
Well, for me…

1027
00:48:23,066 --> 00:48:24,526
I mean, I've…

1028
00:48:26,445 --> 00:48:28,113
I've done all I can, really.

1029
00:48:29,656 --> 00:48:33,160
I was a little jealous.

1030
00:48:33,243 --> 00:48:36,747
Yeah. Um, I am a little jealous,
to be honest.

1031
00:48:36,830 --> 00:48:39,875
We both matched on the Three-way Date too.

1032
00:48:40,751 --> 00:48:42,419
Yeah, I was a little anxious.

1033
00:48:47,799 --> 00:48:50,218
- Is it day seven?
- How is it already day seven?

1034
00:48:53,972 --> 00:48:56,642
Jae-seo, where have you been?

1035
00:48:56,725 --> 00:48:59,102
- Oh, it's cold.
- Man, it's cold!

1036
00:49:00,479 --> 00:49:01,813
KIM JAE-SEO
CHOI HYUK-JOON

1037
00:49:01,897 --> 00:49:04,816
Surely we can talk about
our makeovers at this point.

1038
00:49:06,234 --> 00:49:07,444
What did you get?

1039
00:49:07,527 --> 00:49:09,696
- Do you have the courage…
- Uh-huh.

1040
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:10,822
…to face the truth?

1041
00:49:10,906 --> 00:49:13,283
Yeah. Why? Did you change gender?

1042
00:49:13,367 --> 00:49:14,785
Pretty close, right?

1043
00:49:14,868 --> 00:49:17,788
- Pretty much. It was huge.
- He underwent a total transformation.

1044
00:49:27,047 --> 00:49:28,048
What is this?

1045
00:49:28,131 --> 00:49:29,716
Photos of me trying on clothes.

1046
00:49:30,300 --> 00:49:32,678
- You grew your beard down to here?
- My beard grows white.

1047
00:49:34,638 --> 00:49:36,890
TRYING ON OUTFITS
BEFORE THE MAKEOVER

1048
00:49:36,974 --> 00:49:38,934
We sponsor their date outfits, right?

1049
00:49:39,768 --> 00:49:41,645
That's why there are these photos.

1050
00:49:41,728 --> 00:49:44,231
- Wow, dude. That's insane.
- A regular person.

1051
00:49:44,314 --> 00:49:46,608
- So did you get hair removal?
- I got waxed.

1052
00:49:46,692 --> 00:49:49,861
Oh, waxed. Wow, that's crazy.

1053
00:49:51,321 --> 00:49:52,781
Wow, dude. Seriously.

1054
00:49:52,864 --> 00:49:54,866
You look freakin' amazing now.

1055
00:49:54,950 --> 00:49:57,411
Once you see this,
you see this in a new light, right?

1056
00:49:57,494 --> 00:49:58,620
Yeah.

1057
00:49:58,704 --> 00:50:00,706
Wow. You're one of a kind.

1058
00:50:03,709 --> 00:50:05,502
Wow, this is the best one yet.

1059
00:50:05,585 --> 00:50:08,714
This is literally the most shocking
transformation out of all of us.

1060
00:50:08,797 --> 00:50:11,216
I mean, for real,
you're like a sleeper agent.

1061
00:50:11,299 --> 00:50:14,761
Wow, that's insane.
You're such a character.

1062
00:50:15,887 --> 00:50:18,015
- Do you want to know something?
- What's that?

1063
00:50:18,098 --> 00:50:21,435
Kim Jae-seo's the first person
in the history of this show to receive

1064
00:50:21,518 --> 00:50:23,603
ongoing makeover sessions
even at the dorm.

1065
00:50:23,687 --> 00:50:26,523
- Oh!
- His hair had to be dyed regularly.

1066
00:50:26,606 --> 00:50:28,525
His white hair kept growing
throughout filming.

1067
00:50:28,608 --> 00:50:30,444
- Wow.
- He's truly one of a kind.

1068
00:50:30,527 --> 00:50:31,862
- Wow.
- That's amazing.

1069
00:50:33,238 --> 00:50:35,365
- Hyun-seo, could we talk?
- Sure.

1070
00:50:35,449 --> 00:50:38,452
- Oh, finally.
- Yes. They need to have a serious talk.

1071
00:50:38,535 --> 00:50:39,536
Resolve this, guys.

1072
00:50:43,665 --> 00:50:46,334
Hyun-seo and I needed to talk,
but there wasn't much time.

1073
00:50:46,418 --> 00:50:48,170
I went straight to Sparks House.

1074
00:50:48,253 --> 00:50:50,505
Then the next day,
I went on a date with Han-ju,

1075
00:50:50,589 --> 00:50:53,175
and then in the evening,
Su-ji asked to talk to me.

1076
00:50:53,258 --> 00:50:55,093
Fortunately, things seem to work out,

1077
00:50:55,177 --> 00:50:56,595
and some time freed up,

1078
00:50:56,678 --> 00:50:58,972
so I found her,
and we were able to connect.

1079
00:50:59,056 --> 00:51:00,348
Good. Good work.

1080
00:51:00,432 --> 00:51:02,559
You know, time really flies.

1081
00:51:02,642 --> 00:51:05,562
Yeah. Do we only have two days left now?

1082
00:51:05,645 --> 00:51:06,855
Mmm.

1083
00:51:07,856 --> 00:51:11,234
So we haven't really talked
about what I talked about with them.

1084
00:51:11,318 --> 00:51:13,070
- That kind of…
- It's true.

1085
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:16,323
But we didn't have time to talk
because you weren't here.

1086
00:51:18,408 --> 00:51:20,952
So what I wanted to say was, uh,

1087
00:51:21,036 --> 00:51:26,124
because we never got the chance
to talk to other people,

1088
00:51:26,208 --> 00:51:30,462
we said we'd try to talk to other people,
and then the following day…

1089
00:51:31,088 --> 00:51:34,883
I was on the Three-way Dates, was it?

1090
00:51:34,966 --> 00:51:36,802
On those dates, for the first time,

1091
00:51:36,885 --> 00:51:39,346
I got to know the girls
who were interested in me.

1092
00:51:39,429 --> 00:51:42,349
And to not even give them

1093
00:51:42,432 --> 00:51:44,017
an opportunity felt like…

1094
00:51:44,601 --> 00:51:45,727
- What?
- How do I say…

1095
00:51:50,065 --> 00:51:51,399
I can't watch this.

1096
00:51:54,528 --> 00:51:55,362
Keep going.

1097
00:51:55,445 --> 00:51:56,363
What?

1098
00:51:56,446 --> 00:52:00,992
They told me
they'd been wanting to talk to me.

1099
00:52:01,660 --> 00:52:02,994
So I thought, "Oh."

1100
00:52:03,078 --> 00:52:07,582
"I was fairly confident
you girls had no interest in me at all."

1101
00:52:08,375 --> 00:52:10,752
"Well, okay, then, you know, let's talk."

1102
00:52:10,836 --> 00:52:14,047
So you went on dates with them
for their sakes?

1103
00:52:14,131 --> 00:52:16,383
Oh, no. I wanted to talk to them too.

1104
00:52:16,466 --> 00:52:18,552
- Oh, I understand.
- Right.

1105
00:52:21,471 --> 00:52:24,891
Anyway, well,
it's not that I don't understand.

1106
00:52:24,975 --> 00:52:27,227
You can keep going as long as you want.

1107
00:52:27,310 --> 00:52:30,772
Sure. Anyway, I wanted to have
a conversation with you,

1108
00:52:30,856 --> 00:52:34,317
but I kind of didn't have any time
yesterday either.

1109
00:52:34,401 --> 00:52:36,236
That's right.
I went to talk to you yesterday,

1110
00:52:36,319 --> 00:52:38,446
but you seemed to be talking
with Su-ji for a long time.

1111
00:52:38,530 --> 00:52:40,323
She's the one who came in.

1112
00:52:40,407 --> 00:52:42,117
- Oh, really?
- She asked to talk to me.

1113
00:52:42,200 --> 00:52:45,620
I was having some chocolate,
thinking maybe someone would come,

1114
00:52:45,704 --> 00:52:49,166
so I waited there just in case,
and Su-ji came in.

1115
00:52:49,249 --> 00:52:50,792
Su-ji entered the room.

1116
00:52:50,876 --> 00:52:53,336
But actually, at the time, I really…

1117
00:52:54,212 --> 00:52:56,840
I actually was hoping to talk to you, but…

1118
00:52:58,091 --> 00:53:00,177
I don't think these words
will ring true to her.

1119
00:53:00,260 --> 00:53:02,345
They won't. It's over.
You can see it in her eyes.

1120
00:53:02,429 --> 00:53:03,430
Yeah.

1121
00:53:03,513 --> 00:53:05,765
- You could've come and grabbed me.
- Exactly.

1122
00:53:05,849 --> 00:53:10,812
But it looked like you were having
a serious conversation with Soo-hyun.

1123
00:53:11,438 --> 00:53:13,815
- So I couldn't just interrupt and…
- Uh…

1124
00:53:13,899 --> 00:53:15,358
Well, weren't you with Soo-hyun?

1125
00:53:15,442 --> 00:53:17,569
Are you really trying to tell me
you're that timid?

1126
00:53:18,361 --> 00:53:20,447
I just barged right in and said,

1127
00:53:21,031 --> 00:53:23,158
"I'm borrowing him for a second.
Hey, come with me."

1128
00:53:23,241 --> 00:53:24,451
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1129
00:53:25,160 --> 00:53:28,413
Everyone else does it too,
both the guys and the girls.

1130
00:53:28,496 --> 00:53:31,499
Yeah, we all do that. You wouldn't know,
since you're in your own room,

1131
00:53:31,583 --> 00:53:34,085
but we all just grab one another
for a chat.

1132
00:53:34,169 --> 00:53:36,880
I think all these things
sound like excuses to her.

1133
00:53:36,963 --> 00:53:39,007
I'm sure she finds them absurd.

1134
00:53:39,799 --> 00:53:41,801
Get to know them as much as you want.

1135
00:53:42,761 --> 00:53:46,431
But if you do too much of it, I…

1136
00:53:47,474 --> 00:53:48,767
I'll be…

1137
00:53:52,938 --> 00:53:56,316
Hyun-seo expressed
herself more directly this time.

1138
00:53:56,399 --> 00:53:58,026
I guess if I had to summarize,

1139
00:53:58,109 --> 00:54:02,948
she was saying she doesn't think that
she'll be able to continue waiting for me

1140
00:54:03,031 --> 00:54:04,616
if I keep on like this.

1141
00:54:04,699 --> 00:54:08,036
So I was like,
"You know, she's really confident."

1142
00:54:08,119 --> 00:54:10,372
You know, strong-minded.

1143
00:54:10,455 --> 00:54:14,584
And I could tell that
she still had a lot of feelings for me.

1144
00:54:16,169 --> 00:54:19,381
He seemed to be wavering a lot.

1145
00:54:19,464 --> 00:54:20,548
That is how she would see him.

1146
00:54:20,632 --> 00:54:22,509
He explained to me

1147
00:54:22,592 --> 00:54:26,888
the reasoning behind going on
all those dates with other girls,

1148
00:54:26,972 --> 00:54:29,182
and his reason was
that he'd wanted to give a chance

1149
00:54:29,849 --> 00:54:32,143
to the girls who were attracted to him.

1150
00:54:32,227 --> 00:54:36,147
Honestly, I'm not sure
what he was thinking when he said that.

1151
00:54:36,231 --> 00:54:38,483
I'm the type of person

1152
00:54:38,566 --> 00:54:41,194
who doesn't get influenced much by others,

1153
00:54:41,278 --> 00:54:43,780
but it seems to me

1154
00:54:43,863 --> 00:54:46,449
that Hyuk-joon is very easily influenced.

1155
00:54:46,533 --> 00:54:49,119
So when someone shows interest in him,

1156
00:54:49,202 --> 00:54:50,662
he seems to just…

1157
00:54:51,371 --> 00:54:53,540
kind of lose his head a little.

1158
00:54:53,623 --> 00:54:55,166
At least, in my opinion.

1159
00:54:55,250 --> 00:54:58,086
So I don't know if he's assuming

1160
00:54:58,169 --> 00:55:00,255
that I'll just stick around
waiting for him

1161
00:55:00,338 --> 00:55:01,923
even if he behaves like that.

1162
00:55:02,007 --> 00:55:05,135
And I'm starting to think
maybe he and I aren't compatible.

1163
00:55:05,218 --> 00:55:08,430
It's kind of frustrating to watch him.

1164
00:55:08,513 --> 00:55:11,224
This could actually be, like,
a turning point.

1165
00:55:11,308 --> 00:55:14,894
It could be a situation where Hyuk-joon
comes full circle and returns to her.

1166
00:55:14,978 --> 00:55:17,731
Ah, yes, the epitome of fairness,
Choi Hyuk-joon.

1167
00:55:19,399 --> 00:55:22,694
It's time for him to make up his mind,
but judging from Hyun-seo's confessional,

1168
00:55:22,777 --> 00:55:25,155
he might not have anywhere
to return to if he's not careful.

1169
00:55:25,238 --> 00:55:27,615
The chances of that
are increasing as we speak.

1170
00:55:27,699 --> 00:55:29,617
It's clear her feelings for him
have cooled a lot.

1171
00:55:29,701 --> 00:55:30,535
Yeah, yeah.

1172
00:55:30,618 --> 00:55:33,413
But it seems like Hyuk-joon
may not have picked up on it yet.

1173
00:55:33,496 --> 00:55:34,706
He's completely oblivious.

1174
00:55:34,789 --> 00:55:36,708
He may think,
"That conversation went well."

1175
00:55:36,791 --> 00:55:38,084
"Phew! Got out of that one."

1176
00:55:38,168 --> 00:55:41,254
I'm so frustrated.
I need a cold shower or something.

1177
00:55:44,674 --> 00:55:46,718
A MESSAGE HAS ARRIVED

1178
00:55:47,510 --> 00:55:48,511
Huh?

1179
00:55:48,595 --> 00:55:49,888
Huh?

1180
00:55:49,971 --> 00:55:52,098
Hey, Hyun-seo, this is unbelievable.

1181
00:55:52,182 --> 00:55:53,391
- What?
- What? What?

1182
00:55:53,475 --> 00:55:54,934
ETERNAL SINGLES' DREAM DATE!

1183
00:55:55,018 --> 00:55:56,644
Wow! Our date is at an amusement park.

1184
00:55:56,728 --> 00:55:58,313
Wow, an amusement park?

1185
00:55:58,396 --> 00:56:01,441
"Today, you will have an
amusement park date in the night session."

1186
00:56:01,524 --> 00:56:03,401
Season 2 is just on a different scale.

1187
00:56:03,485 --> 00:56:05,737
They left us school uniforms to wear.

1188
00:56:06,988 --> 00:56:10,200
- Oh, school uniforms?
- A date in school uniforms? So cute.

1189
00:56:10,283 --> 00:56:11,284
Wow.

1190
00:56:11,910 --> 00:56:13,870
It's a real school uniform.

1191
00:56:13,953 --> 00:56:15,955
It's identical to my high-school uniform.

1192
00:56:16,039 --> 00:56:19,250
Oh, my God. This must be
the Eternal Singles' School.

1193
00:56:19,334 --> 00:56:21,294
I guess we're classmates now.

1194
00:56:22,003 --> 00:56:24,172
I really want to go on a date
to an amusement park,

1195
00:56:24,255 --> 00:56:26,216
and in a school uniform.

1196
00:56:26,299 --> 00:56:31,388
I want to go to an amusement park
in a school uniform before I get older.

1197
00:56:31,471 --> 00:56:34,766
One of my dreams was to go
to an amusement park in a school uniform,

1198
00:56:34,849 --> 00:56:36,184
so I was really excited.

1199
00:56:36,267 --> 00:56:38,937
Oh, man, it's been so long
since I wore a school uniform.

1200
00:56:39,020 --> 00:56:40,397
I bet this is gonna be a blast.

1201
00:56:40,480 --> 00:56:43,691
I felt like I was the female lead
in one of those childish drama shows,

1202
00:56:43,775 --> 00:56:45,735
like <i>Boys Over Flowers </i>or <i>The Heirs</i>.

1203
00:56:45,819 --> 00:56:48,738
- Yeah, I get that. That's right.
- A lot of people want to do that.

1204
00:56:48,822 --> 00:56:50,615
It's something you can only do
at this age, right?

1205
00:56:50,698 --> 00:56:51,699
That's right.

1206
00:56:51,783 --> 00:56:54,702
A blast from the past.
It's basically that show, <i>Inheritors</i>.

1207
00:56:54,786 --> 00:56:57,080
"At this school of Satan's,

1208
00:56:57,789 --> 00:56:59,040
Lucifer has arrived."

1209
00:56:59,124 --> 00:57:01,501
This is gonna get interesting.

1210
00:57:01,584 --> 00:57:04,170
Well, how's this for a fit?
What do you think?

1211
00:57:04,254 --> 00:57:05,797
- Whoa, Jung-yun.
- Whoa.

1212
00:57:06,423 --> 00:57:09,843
I'm sure everyone looks really young
when they put on a school uniform.

1213
00:57:09,926 --> 00:57:11,469
- They kinda do.
- Seriously.

1214
00:57:11,553 --> 00:57:13,930
I mean, I don't even look like a teacher.

1215
00:57:14,013 --> 00:57:16,516
I could be, like, the security guard
sitting in the guard shack.

1216
00:57:16,599 --> 00:57:20,061
Oh, he's right.
Not everyone looks young, huh?

1217
00:57:20,145 --> 00:57:22,147
He looks like a Chinese teacher.

1218
00:57:29,112 --> 00:57:30,488
I'm screwed.

1219
00:57:30,572 --> 00:57:34,242
Uh, honestly, I felt a little guilty.
I wasn't comfortable with it.

1220
00:57:34,325 --> 00:57:37,287
The last time I wore
a school uniform was in 2008,

1221
00:57:37,370 --> 00:57:40,623
around 17… 17 years ago.

1222
00:57:40,707 --> 00:57:44,127
I never thought I'd be doing
something like this today.

1223
00:57:44,627 --> 00:57:46,796
- Hello.
- Hey.

1224
00:57:46,880 --> 00:57:49,174
Oh, these guys look good in them.

1225
00:57:49,924 --> 00:57:52,093
We're the only ones
who look like total delinquents.

1226
00:57:52,177 --> 00:57:53,761
This type is needed too.

1227
00:57:53,845 --> 00:57:55,805
Do you wanna join us delinquents, Jae-seo?

1228
00:57:55,889 --> 00:57:58,057
What do you mean, delinquent?
All I did was study.

1229
00:57:58,141 --> 00:58:00,226
The last time I wore these was in 2008.

1230
00:58:00,310 --> 00:58:02,312
- Oh, my God.
- That's crazy.

1231
00:58:02,979 --> 00:58:06,357
Right, I forgot. Science high schools
don't make you wear uniforms, do they?

1232
00:58:06,441 --> 00:58:07,650
Oh, that's why.

1233
00:58:07,734 --> 00:58:10,028
Hey, what grade and class are you in?

1234
00:58:10,111 --> 00:58:13,114
- In the 3rd grade, class 2.
- Oh, 3rd grade, class 2?

1235
00:58:13,198 --> 00:58:15,450
- Let's go. Come on, hurry.
- Let's go.

1236
00:58:16,117 --> 00:58:17,869
Hey, guys. Look over there.

1237
00:58:17,952 --> 00:58:20,997
- Wow! It's an amusement park.
- Oh, my gosh!

1238
00:58:21,080 --> 00:58:24,083
Renting out an amusement park
has been on my bucket list.

1239
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:26,127
It's empty.
They must've rented out the whole place.

1240
00:58:26,211 --> 00:58:29,005
- Wow, we've really gone all out.
- I know.

1241
00:58:29,088 --> 00:58:31,049
- Wow, this is cool.
- This is pretty.

1242
00:58:31,132 --> 00:58:33,092
- So pretty.
- Wow! My goodness.

1243
00:58:33,176 --> 00:58:35,053
I'm shaking with anticipation.

1244
00:58:35,136 --> 00:58:37,514
Same here. I'm so happy. Oh my God!

1245
00:58:37,597 --> 00:58:40,099
Wow, I've never been to
an amusement park that's been rented out.

1246
00:58:40,183 --> 00:58:41,726
I know. I'm so jealous.

1247
00:58:41,809 --> 00:58:44,395
- I'm so excited.
- Yeah. Oh, I'm so excited.

1248
00:58:44,479 --> 00:58:47,023
- Wow, what's that?
- Wow.

1249
00:58:47,106 --> 00:58:48,149
What's that?

1250
00:58:48,233 --> 00:58:49,526
WELCOME ETERNAL SINGLES

1251
00:58:49,609 --> 00:58:51,819
- Oh, my God.
- Oh, my goodness.

1252
00:58:51,903 --> 00:58:52,779
Wow.

1253
00:58:52,862 --> 00:58:54,364
THIS AMUSEMENT PARK DATE
YOU'VE BEEN DREAMING OF

1254
00:58:54,447 --> 00:58:55,281
IS ABOUT TO COME TRUE

1255
00:59:01,996 --> 00:59:04,082
- Oh, I can't watch that.
- Don't do this.

1256
00:59:04,165 --> 00:59:06,084
Oh, please don't do this.

1257
00:59:06,167 --> 00:59:09,754
- It's so nice to see them smile like this.
- Oh, they really look so happy.

1258
00:59:09,837 --> 00:59:10,755
Yeah.

1259
00:59:10,838 --> 00:59:12,173
Oh, this is so funny.

1260
00:59:12,257 --> 00:59:13,383
YOU ARE THE LEAD CHARACTERS

1261
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:15,093
REVEL IN THE ROMANCE
AND EXCITEMENT

1262
00:59:17,262 --> 00:59:18,304
What's going on?

1263
00:59:18,388 --> 00:59:20,098
I have to admit, this is so romantic.

1264
00:59:20,181 --> 00:59:22,267
- Yeah, this is romantic, actually.
- Yeah.

1265
00:59:23,226 --> 00:59:24,352
Are those headbands?

1266
00:59:24,435 --> 00:59:26,688
- Oh! There are headbands.
- Oh, you're right.

1267
00:59:26,771 --> 00:59:29,190
Oh, for couples.
To make it obvious they're a couple.

1268
00:59:29,274 --> 00:59:30,692
Time to strategize.

1269
00:59:30,775 --> 00:59:32,694
They need to watch one another carefully.

1270
00:59:32,777 --> 00:59:35,446
They have to look at who's picking what
before they make their choice.

1271
00:59:38,408 --> 00:59:40,660
- Are they all different?
- Which one do you guys want?

1272
00:59:40,743 --> 00:59:42,412
What'll you pick?

1273
00:59:42,495 --> 00:59:43,830
When I saw them,

1274
00:59:43,913 --> 00:59:46,791
it did occur to me
that we might be split into teams.

1275
00:59:46,874 --> 00:59:48,751
I wanted to be with Su-ji, yes.

1276
00:59:48,835 --> 00:59:52,088
I waited to see what she was picking
before making my choice.

1277
00:59:52,171 --> 00:59:55,550
I hung back and looked over
to see what Jeong-eun had picked,

1278
00:59:55,633 --> 00:59:58,970
but I couldn't see, so I just decided
to leave it to fate and grabbed one.

1279
00:59:59,053 --> 01:00:00,346
- I know.
- This one?

1280
01:00:00,430 --> 01:00:01,639
Oh!

1281
01:00:01,723 --> 01:00:04,017
"Please team up
and enjoy your date with the…"

1282
01:00:04,642 --> 01:00:07,061
Oh, with the people
who picked the same headband.

1283
01:00:07,145 --> 01:00:08,229
Let's go.

1284
01:00:08,313 --> 01:00:09,480
- Shall we go?
- Let's go.

1285
01:00:09,564 --> 01:00:11,524
- Let's go, Mr. Bear.
- Let's go.

1286
01:00:11,608 --> 01:00:12,692
Oh! Let's go.

1287
01:00:12,775 --> 01:00:14,902
TEAM BEAR - JIN-WOO, JEONG-EUN,
SOO-HYUN, JAE-SEO

1288
01:00:14,986 --> 01:00:16,696
Ooh, they are together.

1289
01:00:16,779 --> 01:00:17,822
That's cute.

1290
01:00:17,905 --> 01:00:18,906
- Cat.
- Oh!

1291
01:00:18,990 --> 01:00:21,701
I wanted to share the date with Jeong-eun,

1292
01:00:21,784 --> 01:00:25,038
so I was really happy that we fortunately
chose the same headband

1293
01:00:25,121 --> 01:00:26,247
and could hang out together.

1294
01:00:26,331 --> 01:00:27,248
That's great.

1295
01:00:27,332 --> 01:00:28,541
Team Cat, over here.

1296
01:00:28,625 --> 01:00:30,209
TEAM CAT - HYUK-JOON, SU-JI,
TAE-HOON, HAN-JU

1297
01:00:30,293 --> 01:00:31,294
Hyuk-joon and Su-ji?

1298
01:00:31,377 --> 01:00:34,213
- Do I look weird? I look okay?
- No, you look totally fine.

1299
01:00:34,297 --> 01:00:37,925
Hyuk-joon was still
somewhat of a mystery to me,

1300
01:00:38,009 --> 01:00:40,011
so I wanted to get to know him better.

1301
01:00:40,094 --> 01:00:41,929
I hoped that spending time on this date

1302
01:00:42,013 --> 01:00:44,641
would bring about some change
in my feelings.

1303
01:00:44,724 --> 01:00:47,435
TEAM DUCK - SEUNG-HYUN,
HYUN-SEO, JUNG-YUN, SEO-YOON

1304
01:00:47,518 --> 01:00:50,980
I wanted to be with Su-ji,
but it didn't work out.

1305
01:00:51,064 --> 01:00:53,483
Obviously, that was pretty disappointing.

1306
01:00:54,317 --> 01:00:56,319
Hyuk-joon and Hyun-seo
are separated again.

1307
01:00:56,402 --> 01:00:58,071
So are Jung-yun and Su-ji.

1308
01:01:00,907 --> 01:01:03,159
- A roller coaster?
- Oh, this is scary.

1309
01:01:10,792 --> 01:01:12,919
I was really happy. I thought,

1310
01:01:13,002 --> 01:01:17,256
"When else would I get to experience
something crazy like this?"

1311
01:01:17,340 --> 01:01:19,300
We're people who are crazy in love.

1312
01:01:19,384 --> 01:01:21,427
- Like this?
- So cute!

1313
01:01:22,053 --> 01:01:24,222
We never got to experience dating,

1314
01:01:24,305 --> 01:01:26,849
something everyone else
in normal life does,

1315
01:01:26,933 --> 01:01:29,477
so this was a really special experience,

1316
01:01:29,560 --> 01:01:32,146
like something straight out
of a Korean drama.

1317
01:01:32,230 --> 01:01:34,065
That's why I loved it so much.

1318
01:01:34,148 --> 01:01:36,025
- Hooray!
- That looks so fun.

1319
01:01:36,109 --> 01:01:38,069
You know, when you're on a ride,

1320
01:01:38,152 --> 01:01:40,947
all you can feel is the nervousness
and excitement.

1321
01:01:41,030 --> 01:01:42,949
It made all my other thoughts disappear.

1322
01:01:43,032 --> 01:01:46,536
And living in this moment
made me feel totally refreshed.

1323
01:01:46,619 --> 01:01:48,287
They're so cute, right?

1324
01:01:48,371 --> 01:01:50,665
- What's this?
- I'm going to buy this one.

1325
01:01:50,748 --> 01:01:51,999
- Isn't this cute?
- Oh, me too.

1326
01:01:52,083 --> 01:01:53,876
- It's cute.
- Throw them all in. I'll pay.

1327
01:01:53,960 --> 01:01:55,586
Jae-seo says he'll pay. He must be loaded.

1328
01:01:55,670 --> 01:01:57,630
- He's Gu Jun-pyo.
- Wow, you're amazing.

1329
01:01:57,714 --> 01:01:59,549
From today on, you're my number one.

1330
01:01:59,632 --> 01:02:01,634
- That's ridiculous.
- Like in <i>Boys over Flowers</i>.

1331
01:02:01,718 --> 01:02:03,052
I like this one.

1332
01:02:03,136 --> 01:02:04,679
WHAT WAS THE MOST
MEMORABLE MOMENT?

1333
01:02:04,762 --> 01:02:07,432
For me, I really liked
the Life4Cuts photo booth.

1334
01:02:07,515 --> 01:02:11,436
It was the first time I had
the opportunity and ever even done it.

1335
01:02:11,519 --> 01:02:15,523
Actually, there's nothing stopping me from
going to one by myself and taking photos,

1336
01:02:15,606 --> 01:02:17,567
but doing it with friends
is a different feeling.

1337
01:02:17,650 --> 01:02:19,819
That's why that was
the most memorable part.

1338
01:02:19,902 --> 01:02:23,030
- Oh, it was his first time ever.
- That's right, yeah.

1339
01:02:23,114 --> 01:02:26,826
Jae-seo hasn't experienced a lot of things
because he's been too busy working.

1340
01:02:26,909 --> 01:02:28,911
- He's made some good friends too.
- Yeah.

1341
01:02:28,995 --> 01:02:31,247
- Friendship and love go hand in hand.
- That's right.

1342
01:02:31,330 --> 01:02:32,957
I think that's it up ahead.

1343
01:02:33,040 --> 01:02:35,251
Oh, it's sparkling.

1344
01:02:35,960 --> 01:02:38,337
Oh! Hyuk-joon and Su-ji
are on the ride together.

1345
01:02:38,421 --> 01:02:42,049
In their school uniforms, they kind
of look like the prom king and queen.

1346
01:02:42,133 --> 01:02:45,595
I'm actually a little worried
because I get motion sickness.

1347
01:02:45,678 --> 01:02:47,680
I get really sick if I go on rides
that spin around.

1348
01:02:47,764 --> 01:02:49,974
- Oh, really?
- So I'm a little nervous.

1349
01:02:50,057 --> 01:02:51,642
Is this what we do, then?

1350
01:02:52,435 --> 01:02:55,021
Time out, please. Let me off, please.

1351
01:02:57,356 --> 01:02:59,859
Ooh, we're moving.

1352
01:02:59,942 --> 01:03:02,361
Why didn't they tell us it was starting?

1353
01:03:02,445 --> 01:03:04,697
- Wait.
- We're moving.

1354
01:03:05,615 --> 01:03:07,492
I'm panicking.

1355
01:03:07,575 --> 01:03:09,410
Won't you get sick from spinning?

1356
01:03:09,494 --> 01:03:11,078
- I kind of want to.
- Yeah?

1357
01:03:11,162 --> 01:03:12,622
- Oh, no.
- I want to get off.

1358
01:03:12,705 --> 01:03:14,373
- Really?
- Hyuk-joon, help me.

1359
01:03:15,333 --> 01:03:17,585
I can't even really ride
Viking ship rides, actually.

1360
01:03:17,668 --> 01:03:18,878
- Oh, really?
- Yeah.

1361
01:03:19,587 --> 01:03:21,464
Maybe you should try
to keep your eyes closed?

1362
01:03:21,547 --> 01:03:23,633
- Should I?
- Yeah, I think that would be better.

1363
01:03:23,716 --> 01:03:24,717
It could help.

1364
01:03:24,801 --> 01:03:26,886
Oh, what is this?

1365
01:03:28,554 --> 01:03:31,015
- Will he hold her hand?
- Something's about to happen.

1366
01:03:31,098 --> 01:03:32,433
Oh, surely not.

1367
01:03:34,936 --> 01:03:36,687
This does make you feel dizzy, actually.

1368
01:03:36,771 --> 01:03:39,357
- Right? I'm feeling a little dizzy.
- It does make you feel dizzy.

1369
01:03:39,440 --> 01:03:41,692
Let's just walk around a little
once we're off.

1370
01:03:41,776 --> 01:03:44,612
See, they're taking care of each other.
That's how you make a heart flutter.

1371
01:03:44,695 --> 01:03:45,822
That's right.

1372
01:03:45,905 --> 01:03:47,907
I underestimated this ride.

1373
01:03:48,991 --> 01:03:51,035
- We can get off of it soon.
- Okay.

1374
01:03:52,578 --> 01:03:55,039
Hyuk-joon took really good care of me.

1375
01:03:55,122 --> 01:03:56,666
I was quite impressed.

1376
01:03:56,749 --> 01:04:00,044
Feeling he was concerned about me
helped me during the ride,

1377
01:04:00,127 --> 01:04:02,296
and it made me feel good.

1378
01:04:03,840 --> 01:04:05,091
This is fun.

1379
01:04:05,174 --> 01:04:07,468
Yeah, this is fun.
I'm really enjoying myself.

1380
01:04:07,552 --> 01:04:09,971
- This is so much fun.
- Just pure fun.

1381
01:04:11,222 --> 01:04:12,723
- Oh! Same place?
- After you.

1382
01:04:14,016 --> 01:04:17,895
Of course Hyuk-joon and Su-ji walk in
together right when Hyun-seo's there.

1383
01:04:17,979 --> 01:04:18,980
Hello.

1384
01:04:19,063 --> 01:04:21,524
No way. You guys are also here?

1385
01:04:21,607 --> 01:04:23,234
Hello, you guys.

1386
01:04:23,985 --> 01:04:25,987
Are you enjoying yourselves?

1387
01:04:26,070 --> 01:04:29,240
- They're here.
- Ah, that'll get Jung-yun flustered too.

1388
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:32,368
- Shall we show them off? Get up, everyone.
- Let's show them off.

1389
01:04:32,451 --> 01:04:35,037
- Hey, do you see this?
- What is it?

1390
01:04:35,121 --> 01:04:37,164
Let's see. What is it?
Did you all get matching ones?

1391
01:04:37,248 --> 01:04:39,333
- Yeah.
- We have them too.

1392
01:04:39,417 --> 01:04:41,335
- Matching couple items.
- We won.

1393
01:04:41,419 --> 01:04:42,920
You can't beat us.

1394
01:04:43,004 --> 01:04:44,797
We took the best photos at Life4Cuts.

1395
01:04:44,881 --> 01:04:47,383
- No way you can beat us.
- Our photos are out of this world.

1396
01:04:47,466 --> 01:04:49,510
- Our photos are amazing.
- Everyone's here.

1397
01:04:50,219 --> 01:04:52,763
- Oh, that's right, that team bought Pingu.
- Hey!

1398
01:04:52,847 --> 01:04:55,600
That's the first thing
those guys are bragging about.

1399
01:04:55,683 --> 01:04:58,394
- Those guys are all about the gear, huh?
- Yeah, they're all about the gear.

1400
01:04:58,477 --> 01:05:00,521
- It's not even that big a deal.
- What do you mean, "bragging"?

1401
01:05:00,605 --> 01:05:01,731
Are you talking about our swag?

1402
01:05:01,814 --> 01:05:03,608
What was that? Oh, don't worry about it.

1403
01:05:03,691 --> 01:05:05,818
What do you mean, "All about the gear"?

1404
01:05:05,902 --> 01:05:08,946
- What do you mean, "All about the gear"?
- Oh, is this psychological warfare?

1405
01:05:09,030 --> 01:05:11,490
Being split into teams is making everyone…

1406
01:05:11,574 --> 01:05:13,868
- Compete with each other.
- We've got spirit.

1407
01:05:13,951 --> 01:05:16,203
- We're the coolest team.
- It's ugly-cute.

1408
01:05:16,287 --> 01:05:18,164
Why would you say that? This is cute-cute.

1409
01:05:18,247 --> 01:05:19,999
This one's basic cute.

1410
01:05:20,082 --> 01:05:21,459
They're both cute.

1411
01:05:21,542 --> 01:05:22,919
They'll be useful.

1412
01:05:25,630 --> 01:05:28,799
Wow, I don't know how long it's been
since I felt like this.

1413
01:05:28,883 --> 01:05:30,885
Like being in high school.

1414
01:05:30,968 --> 01:05:32,261
- I know.
- Yeah.

1415
01:05:32,345 --> 01:05:35,848
It doesn't feel like a date,
but it's so fun.

1416
01:05:35,932 --> 01:05:38,142
Rather than a date, it feels
like I'm hanging out with friends,

1417
01:05:38,225 --> 01:05:39,518
but it's so much fun.

1418
01:05:44,357 --> 01:05:48,235
It did feel like the only goal
was to have fun, actually.

1419
01:05:48,319 --> 01:05:49,987
Honestly for me,

1420
01:05:50,613 --> 01:05:54,325
I don't really like rides
because I'm scared of them, so…

1421
01:05:54,408 --> 01:05:57,161
- So he's not too happy about this.
- This is fun!

1422
01:05:57,244 --> 01:05:59,622
- The last one was nothing.
- The last one was nothing.

1423
01:05:59,705 --> 01:06:01,374
This is it, Jin-woo! This is it!

1424
01:06:01,457 --> 01:06:03,960
Oh, Jin-woo didn't go on the rides.

1425
01:06:04,043 --> 01:06:06,545
And this was his chance
to sit next to Jeong-eun.

1426
01:06:06,629 --> 01:06:09,173
It was a bit of a shame.
I was disappointed

1427
01:06:09,256 --> 01:06:12,593
that I didn't get to spend
more time with Jeong-eun alone.

1428
01:06:12,677 --> 01:06:14,178
- Yeah.
- Too bad.

1429
01:06:18,849 --> 01:06:20,393
What would you want to do tomorrow?

1430
01:06:20,476 --> 01:06:22,144
Yeah, what do you hope we'll do?

1431
01:06:22,228 --> 01:06:24,063
We're almost at the end.

1432
01:06:24,146 --> 01:06:26,565
- We only have Friday and Saturday.
- Yeah.

1433
01:06:26,649 --> 01:06:29,777
At this point, anything other than
selecting your own date partner

1434
01:06:29,860 --> 01:06:30,987
is kind of pointless.

1435
01:06:32,029 --> 01:06:35,491
And not just selecting,
but mutually selecting each other.

1436
01:06:35,574 --> 01:06:38,577
Outside of that,
I'm not sure there's anything worth doing.

1437
01:06:41,831 --> 01:06:44,333
I think we should just keep doing
what we can.

1438
01:06:44,417 --> 01:06:46,961
I think the right thing to do
is just go for it rather than wondering,

1439
01:06:47,044 --> 01:06:48,087
"Should I or shouldn't I?"

1440
01:06:48,170 --> 01:06:49,171
That's true.

1441
01:06:52,717 --> 01:06:56,053
Jin-woo was talking about
how he was going to do

1442
01:06:56,137 --> 01:06:58,389
everything in his power tomorrow

1443
01:06:58,472 --> 01:07:00,641
regardless of the potential outcome.

1444
01:07:01,267 --> 01:07:02,727
But for me,

1445
01:07:02,810 --> 01:07:05,938
it's not that I find him unpleasant

1446
01:07:06,022 --> 01:07:08,858
or that I find him lacking in any way,

1447
01:07:08,941 --> 01:07:12,486
but the one thing that does weigh on me
is that he's a student.

1448
01:07:13,070 --> 01:07:14,780
Practicality matters.

1449
01:07:14,864 --> 01:07:18,701
Since the relationship doesn't end
with the show,

1450
01:07:19,410 --> 01:07:24,665
um, that aspect is what's been
troubling me quite a lot since yesterday.

1451
01:07:24,749 --> 01:07:27,793
And for this reason,
I couldn't really respond to him

1452
01:07:27,877 --> 01:07:29,628
in any substantial way.

1453
01:07:30,337 --> 01:07:34,008
All I could do while I was sitting
in front of him was look down,

1454
01:07:34,091 --> 01:07:36,010
stabbing at the ice in my drink.

1455
01:07:40,056 --> 01:07:43,601
The most significant lesson here
is there's no way to control who I like.

1456
01:07:43,684 --> 01:07:45,811
- There's no way, no matter what you do.
- So true.

1457
01:07:47,521 --> 01:07:50,441
Jeong-eun kind of looks like
she feels bad for him.

1458
01:07:50,524 --> 01:07:53,402
Wow, she's already thinking
about the practical side of things.

1459
01:07:54,195 --> 01:07:56,530
Especially because she's in her 30s, so…
it could matter.

1460
01:07:56,614 --> 01:07:58,824
This is something
she needs to think deeply about.

1461
01:07:58,908 --> 01:08:01,327
I think this shows
that they're taking this seriously.

1462
01:08:01,410 --> 01:08:02,787
- That's right.
- I agree.

1463
01:08:02,870 --> 01:08:04,705
It's not just, "Oh, I had fun
and enjoyed myself."

1464
01:08:04,789 --> 01:08:06,248
"Thank you very much," and that's it.

1465
01:08:06,332 --> 01:08:09,794
They're giving serious thought
to the specifics of how things will work

1466
01:08:09,877 --> 01:08:11,420
if they actually start dating.

1467
01:08:11,504 --> 01:08:13,714
- Let's look at our photos again.
- Okay.

1468
01:08:13,798 --> 01:08:16,217
- We're so proud of them, aren't we?
- Yeah. Oh, I love them.

1469
01:08:16,300 --> 01:08:18,427
- For a start, we all look so good.
- We do.

1470
01:08:18,511 --> 01:08:21,388
Because we're minimalists.
Those guys are all about the swag.

1471
01:08:21,472 --> 01:08:24,558
- Look at this!
- "Marie Kondo." They look so good.

1472
01:08:24,642 --> 01:08:26,268
Oh, the vibe here is nice.

1473
01:08:26,352 --> 01:08:29,647
I think it's the first time in
my life that I look this good in a photo.

1474
01:08:29,730 --> 01:08:31,774
- I'm serious.
- They look really good.

1475
01:08:31,857 --> 01:08:33,192
We have the best teamwork.

1476
01:08:33,275 --> 01:08:35,319
- Hyun-seo looks really unwell.
- Yeah.

1477
01:08:35,402 --> 01:08:37,988
She can hear everything.
Because they're being loud about it.

1478
01:08:38,072 --> 01:08:40,533
We're always glowing.

1479
01:08:40,616 --> 01:08:43,702
Hyun-seo is totally tuned in
to their conversation.

1480
01:08:43,786 --> 01:08:45,371
Her ears are perked up behind her.

1481
01:08:45,454 --> 01:08:47,540
All her attention
is on what they're saying.

1482
01:08:47,623 --> 01:08:51,752
I would be lying if I said
I wasn't paying attention to Hyuk-joon.

1483
01:08:51,836 --> 01:08:54,797
I couldn't seem to pull myself away,

1484
01:08:54,880 --> 01:08:59,552
but it's impossible not to notice someone
when they're kind of right there.

1485
01:08:59,635 --> 01:09:01,762
- That's right.
- Of course.

1486
01:09:01,846 --> 01:09:04,807
It did make me wonder
if he was having fun.

1487
01:09:09,562 --> 01:09:11,230
Looks like they're in a good mood.

1488
01:09:11,313 --> 01:09:13,649
- That innocent psycho look.
- "Innocent."

1489
01:09:27,830 --> 01:09:29,498
- Oh, Su-ji.
- Huh, what's wrong?

1490
01:09:29,582 --> 01:09:30,708
What's up with her?

1491
01:09:30,791 --> 01:09:33,878
Oh, that's what I wanted to ask.
Age difference.

1492
01:09:33,961 --> 01:09:35,171
- Age difference?
- Yeah.

1493
01:09:35,254 --> 01:09:38,007
The biggest acceptable age gap
between you and your partner.

1494
01:09:38,090 --> 01:09:40,176
Like, how many years older or younger.

1495
01:09:40,259 --> 01:09:43,179
My preference has always been
one year younger.

1496
01:09:43,262 --> 01:09:46,515
Because anyone younger than that
would feel like a little sister.

1497
01:09:46,599 --> 01:09:47,725
Oh.

1498
01:09:48,309 --> 01:09:50,436
So more like a little sister
than a girlfriend.

1499
01:09:51,645 --> 01:09:52,980
Yeah.

1500
01:09:53,063 --> 01:09:54,565
I see.

1501
01:09:56,025 --> 01:09:57,026
Hmm.

1502
01:09:57,651 --> 01:09:58,903
For me…

1503
01:09:59,653 --> 01:10:02,156
- Oh, it's my turn. I…
- Why is she so out of it?

1504
01:10:02,239 --> 01:10:04,909
Uh, I think I'm okay with up to…

1505
01:10:04,992 --> 01:10:07,286
five years older than me.

1506
01:10:07,369 --> 01:10:09,455
Su-ji and Hyuk-joon have
a five-year age gap.

1507
01:10:09,538 --> 01:10:11,415
She must be saying that for him, right?

1508
01:10:11,498 --> 01:10:14,627
Because there are people with whom
you don't feel the age gap so much.

1509
01:10:14,710 --> 01:10:17,129
- Happens a lot.
- Yeah, so that's why.

1510
01:10:25,763 --> 01:10:28,349
At the end of the evening,
in the restaurant,

1511
01:10:28,432 --> 01:10:30,517
we were having a conversation, and…

1512
01:10:32,061 --> 01:10:34,521
I just felt like I couldn't even
look him in the eye.

1513
01:10:35,022 --> 01:10:37,024
I think this environment
is uncomfortable for her.

1514
01:10:37,107 --> 01:10:38,567
I wonder what it is.

1515
01:10:40,861 --> 01:10:43,781
It's like, with Jung-yun,
I feel completely at ease,

1516
01:10:43,864 --> 01:10:45,866
but when I'm looking at Hyuk-joon,

1517
01:10:46,533 --> 01:10:49,245
I just find it difficult
to make eye contact with him.

1518
01:10:49,328 --> 01:10:51,997
It felt so awkward,
but I really don't know why.

1519
01:10:52,081 --> 01:10:53,332
What is it?

1520
01:10:53,415 --> 01:10:55,417
If you can't look someone in the eye,

1521
01:10:55,501 --> 01:10:57,169
that's what it means, right?

1522
01:10:57,253 --> 01:11:00,923
So I was thinking to myself,
"Why am I nervous with Hyuk-joon?"

1523
01:11:03,425 --> 01:11:06,971
I felt like the part of me
that I thought I'd turned away from

1524
01:11:07,054 --> 01:11:09,014
was kind of coming back up to the surface.

1525
01:11:13,102 --> 01:11:14,728
Right now, my first choice

1526
01:11:15,354 --> 01:11:16,438
is Hyuk-joon.

1527
01:11:17,439 --> 01:11:20,401
I'm in big trouble. I guess
I'll probably end up choosing Hyuk-joon.

1528
01:11:20,484 --> 01:11:22,236
You've been on dates with so many women.

1529
01:11:22,319 --> 01:11:25,322
I'm sure it must be very confusing
to keep track of your conversations.

1530
01:11:25,406 --> 01:11:27,574
I've decided to just go for it.

1531
01:11:27,658 --> 01:11:29,618
No more hesitating on my part.

1532
01:11:29,702 --> 01:11:30,995
Hello.

1533
01:11:31,078 --> 01:11:34,498
I think the mere fact that I was talking
to someone I was interested in

1534
01:11:34,581 --> 01:11:35,791
made me nervous.
